Text1_lang: Ah, we have reached our first stop. Circle the wagons, Shikaar. It is time for a hunt.

Text_lang: The Horn of Drusahl will be visible once we cross the bridge. You must see it, two-foot!
Ah, yes. The Horn represents the ancient pact formed by Teera and a green dragon named Merithra. Their friendship ended a long enmity between dragons and Maruuk.

Afterward, the centaur hunted the plains, and the dragons tended the gardens. But they agreed to help one another in times of need. The Horn of Drusahl was built as a physical manifestation of their oath.

Text1_lang: But then, the dragons left. And after ten thousand years, they return to these lands! I am interested to hear what the Khanam Matra says about that.
We are guided by Ohn'ahra, Tomul. It was she who granted us these lands, who arbitrated with the dragons. She knows the way.
Ohn'ahra, the Windmother, is the ancestor of all ohuna. She led our founders, Maruuk and Teera, to the plains. My clanmates interpret her songs to advise our people.
Hold! I hear her call. Ohn'ahra will sing to me here.

Text_lang: Maruukai is just ahead. It is a grand and sacred meeting place. Centaur from all around the plains gather there.
Each season we meet for the Khural, a time of truce and communion. Clans large and small come together, sharing our resources and our stories.

Text1_lang: I do look forward to reconnecting to my peers. Perhaps Tigari Khan can help me decipher this omen from the river.
I am going to avoid the Nokhud. They antagonize everyone at these things.

Text_lang: The rest of the Shikaar should have already arrived from the other camps. Our rise should be well settled by the time we arrive.
It seems the other clans beat us here. Between our outsider and the green dragon emissary, this should be a Khural to remember.

Text1_lang: Dark Talons, fall in!
Lead the way, Ebyssian.
The Warders will follow Wrathion.
Thank goodness.
Mother...
[DNT] <Mirthful sigh.>
We have to leave the Reach.
Now!
Let the winds carry us onward! The Emerald Gardens will fall!

Text_lang: Ah, young Wrathion. I owe you my thanks--
Your help was invaluable in securing my rightful place on the Obsidian Throne.
Oh... I believe you are mistaken--this throne, this legacy--is my birthright.
No. The mistake is yours. I was anointed caretaker of this flight by Neltharion himself.
So let me be clear... when all is said and done, I will be the Aspect of the black dragonflight.
Is that so? May the worthiest dragon win.

Text1_lang: Halt!

Text_lang: Get away from... do not...

Text1_lang: Is this what passes for a mystic of the Maruuk?
Ysera, your flight needs you.
We need you.
Whatever the price may be for your return to Azeroth, name it.

Text_lang: Tyrande...
Ohn'ahra... I am sorry.

Text1_lang: Tell us!

Text_lang: It's me.
I must be the one to stay.

Text1_lang: What?

Text_lang: Ysera knows this--though she would never ask it of me.

Text1_lang: No.
Pathetic.
We will find another way.

Text_lang: When she gave her life for mine in Val'sharah, it was not her time.
And now... the balance may be restored.

Text1_lang: Then... then I will stay as well.
Shandris and the others can...

Text_lang: Tyrande...
Should everything we hope come to pass, the Kaldorei will need you.

Text1_lang: I am so tired, Malfurion.
Do not ask this of me.
After everything we have endured...

Text_lang: My love.
You have always been the strength of our people.
They will follow you ever onward, and you will never be alone.

Text1_lang: Until I see you again...
I will dream of the night we may truly rest... together.
How is this possible...
The Maruuk, too, have been plagued by these Primalists.
If Ohn'ahra wills it, I will blow the Horn of Drusahl on the morrow to signal our accord with the green dragonflight.
Merithra, daughter of Ysera, is grateful for your...

Text_lang: Grateful? Ha! Dragons only respect dragons.
No Maruuk blood will be spilled for them.

Text1_lang: You are not the Khanam Matra, Balakar.

Text_lang: A true leader would never surrender this land to outsiders.
You desecrate the memory of Maruuk Thousandbones, Sarest.

Text1_lang: Stand down!

Text_lang: No. These plains belong to the Maruuk.
And Maruukai belongs to the Nokhud!
We'll hold them off as best as we can until he arrives. Hurry!
I... hope that worked. I need my flight.

Text1_lang: We will see in due time.

Text_lang: Khadgar--what's happened?
The Primalists are on the move!
It seems we did far too well at stymieing their efforts at Vakthros.
Raszageth has renewed the attack herself!

Text1_lang: If Vakthros falls, the whole of the Azure Span will fall with it.

Text_lang: Quickly then! We must stop her, before all is lost!
Hopefully we won't have to face her alone.

Text1_lang: Weakling... you need a mortal to defend you!
Abominations, both of you... and you will perish here, cold and alone!

Text_lang: He is not alone!

Text1_lang: You have failed, "Aspect". You will soon learn that killing you would have been a mercy.
Now you can watch your empire collapse alongside your false queen.

Text_lang: Hmm...

Text1_lang: Let us face this enemy together.
Majordomo, protect the eggs below while I distract Raszageth. She will not harm our young!
[DNT][TEST] TimeKellyEvent 10.0!
Destroy the artifact? No! Don't you see? Now that I know where it is, we can use its power to end all the enemies of the Kirin Tor!
The power will consume you like it consumed the others! It must be destroyed.
No. You will thank me upon my return. I will bring peace to the Azure Span!

Text_lang: To'tik... $n... what do we do?

Text1_lang: We destroy the artifact.

Text_lang: Thank you... now we are free.
Text1_lang: Thank you... now we are free.
Please... warn others of my tale. Ensure no one else makes my mistake.
Our ambush was a success.
Go now, infuse them with the elements.
Work quickly.
The convoy yielded enough eggs to begin.
Wash away the stain of Order.
Outsiders have come ashore.
We cannot let them interfere!

Text_lang: Hail and well met, friends.
I apologize if I startled you. Our arcane wards were activated and I felt obliged to investigate.
My name is Khadgar, Archmage of the Kirin Tor.
Is that so? Well, come see me in camp. We'll try and find the answers you seek.
We are not your friends, mage.
That's how they get you.

Text1_lang: Easy now, Telash.
I am Scalecommander Emberthal of the Dracthyr. My companions are $p and Telash Greywing.
We are... new to this area. We come seeking information.
He seemed pleasant.

Text_lang: Over there!
Let's get this over with.
Text1_lang: Let's get this over with.

Text_lang: Yes, there it is!
Text1_lang: Yes, there it is!

Text_lang: Oh! Pretty!
Text1_lang: Oh! Pretty!

Text_lang: OW!
Text1_lang: OW!

Text_lang: No!
Text1_lang: No!

Text_lang: It's--it's okay, it's going to be alright. It's just a little mana burn...
Text1_lang: It's--it's okay, it's going to be alright. It's just a little mana burn...

Text_lang: I do not believe any of this. Lies... all lies! You wanted us locked away in cages.

Text1_lang: Young one, I assure you I had no idea. Nor did the rest of my flight.

Text_lang: Liar! You aren't even real! Merely a spell... yet another falsehood!
I'll find what you are hiding, illusion. And when I do, the world will know the truth!

Text1_lang: My beloved Malygos, why did you inflict such pain on so many?

Text_lang: Nezzie cries.
Text1_lang: Nezzie cries.
Forgive me, I was distracted. You wish to continue your research--allow me to unlock the rest of these tomes for you.
Greetings.

Text_lang: Gah! Not again!

Text1_lang: Well, aren't we an excitable bunch? What brings you to my... the archives?
We are looking for information on our captivity at the hands of the blue dragon Malygos.
Ah... Perhaps I can be of assistance after all.

Text_lang: Enough talk! We demand answers, phantom.
Don't worry! It's not the first time something up here has exploded like that. We've got tough scales!
Text1_lang: Don't worry! It's not the first time something up here has exploded like that. We've got tough scales!

Text_lang: What? The wild magic is up here, too? You've been hurt?
Text1_lang: What? The wild magic is up here, too? You've been hurt?

Text_lang: Oh-! Uh, no--no! Nobody's been hurt, we're totally safe alone up here! Don't... don't send us away...
Text1_lang: Oh-! Uh, no--no! Nobody's been hurt, we're totally safe alone up here! Don't... don't send us away...

Text_lang: You're children! Even I know children shouldn't be left unsupervised...
Text1_lang: You're children! Even I know children shouldn't be left unsupervised...
Almost there....

Text_lang: <Pained groan.>
<Shocked gasp.>
Excellent! You've found another misaligned ley line. Restoring the uninterrupted flow of magic is crucial for the Azure Span's recovery.
Thank you, $n. Each ley line we restore contributes to the health of the Dragon Isles as a whole.

Text1_lang: <breath>
<Breathing heavily>
<breath>
<breath>
<Sighs>
<breath>
I believe we can channel the essence of each into the Mother Oathstone and restore our aspectral powers.

Text_lang: <Tell Shaw to signal his informant.>
Text1_lang: <Tell Shaw to signal his informant.>
Until I see you again...

Text_lang: No reparation is enough! The Stonemasons deserve every coin in every coffer of Stormwind city! Clessington will lead us there!

Text1_lang: Duncon?! You weren't even a Stonemason! You joined to be a thief!

Text_lang: So you finally show yourself, VanCleef. And with a Stormwind dog in tow! See, Defias? See how she will make us all lapdogs of Stormwind?!
We muster in Northshire! Join us, and we march on Stormwind! For the Defias!
For the Defias!
Text1_lang: For the Defias!
The amulet!

Text_lang: |cffdb453dRequires: Primal Mote|r
Text1_lang: |cffdb453dRequires: Primal Mote|r

Text_lang: |cff34ccebRequires: Primal Mote|r
Text1_lang: |cff34ccebRequires: Primal Mote|r
Grandfather, why are you still tasked with updating these graves? Surely it should go to younger drakes.

Text_lang: Wait, something isn't right...
... Vanessa.

Text1_lang: Noticed my little sleight of hand, did you? No way I'm leaving something like this for Stormwind. The Drakefire Amulet is mine, now.

Text_lang: I don't think so, VanCleef! Hand it over!

Text1_lang: Oh?! You just want its power, just like everyone else!
Wh-what is happening?

Text_lang: Here they are now. Greetings Kalecgos, and to you, Life-Binder.
Senegos nudges Stellagosa to bow.

Text1_lang: Ah, Senegos. I saw the remnants of your arcane ball. I am heartened to see you have not forgotten your old ways.
Kalecgos, you may do the honors to lay the essences of Malygos and Sindragosa to rest.

Text_lang: Thank you. Sindragosa... Malygos... I am sorry it took us so long to give you this peace.
May you have the rest now you were robbed of in life.
How strange... are these remnants from Malygos and Sindragosa's past?

Text1_lang: It would seem so. It appears they were unable to truly depart from this world when they were slain.

Text_lang: I saw many strange phenomenon such as this when I laid to rest the blue dragons that made it back here from Neltharion's betrayal.

Text1_lang: It was a tragedy that so many were killed... including Sindragosa. Even then, the Lich King allowed her no rest. It pained me to see her raised into undeath.

Text_lang: [DEPRECIATED] I hoped against hope that I would see her return. When word reached my brood of what happened to her thousands of years later...
I could not believe it when word reached my brood of what happened to her. It is a small blessing that she did not linger for long in such a state.
Sindragosa and Malygos both deserved better. I hope now we have given them their proper rest.
I will stay here to monitor the situation with the others... and speak to Senegos on a matter concerning his brood.
It should only be a moment of your time, Kalecgos. Stellagosa, Emmigosa, you will want to be here as well.

Text1_lang: Of course, Grandfather. Whatever you need.

Text_lang: Good. You're here.
I would just as soon never set foot in a creche again.
Emberthal awaits you inside.
Oh, and... (clears throat)... thank you. For aiding us.

Text1_lang: Damos speaks highly of you...
Not something he does often.
He and the others are looking for answers... a reason for all of this.
After everything that's happened, everything we've been through...
I'm beginning to wonder if... (sigh)... what I'm looking for isn't here.
Oh no... No...

Text_lang: (death rattle)
Begone. The Reach belongs to the Sundered Flame.

Text1_lang: SARKARETH!
Damos...
(labored heavy breathing, grief turning to rage, building in determination)

Text_lang: Sindragosa and Malygos should be at rest. Yet their anger is growing larger by the moment.
Maybe they want things settled? Didn't they both die very violently?

Text1_lang: Like the spirits of Crystalsong Forest... Sindragosa and Malygos are stranded in their final moments of death.
And now they are reliving those final moments of their lives in an endless loop.
Perhaps all of this chaos was their only way of getting our attention? Wildly lashing out, hoping someone would hear them.

Text_lang: Well we certainly hear them, and we are going to help. $n, recover their essences. We are taking them back to the Azure Archives.
Emberthal!
Leaving me behind? Well, I suppose I am a dragon after all!

Text1_lang: Look around you! Can you see why I fell in love with Pandaria?

Text_lang: It's beautiful!

Text1_lang: Better than frost and snow! Keep up, Kalecgos! Let the warm winds take you.

Text_lang: Haha!

Text1_lang: That boy still has it, doesn't he?

Text_lang: Where are we going?

Text1_lang: My home!
My home.

Text_lang: <Sniff> So many papers... So many papers tae write! It's beautiful! Ach, I knew ye could do it!
Oh, this gives me an idea for a commemorative wood carving that'd sell like frostcakes!
Text1_lang: Oh, this gives me an idea for a commemorative wood carving that'd sell like frostcakes!
I knew I liked you for a reason. Say, $n... If you get tired of talking, there're always more beasts to hunt!

Text_lang: The tribes are united once again. Thank you, $p.
A new home...
Text1_lang: A new home...

Text_lang: For $p! For the Winterpelt!
Text1_lang: For $p! For the Winterpelt!

Text_lang: When I was young... the centaur took me.
It was Bovan who found me, and aided in my rescue.
Without him, I never would have...
It was my turn to rescue him.
And they have robbed me of it.
<Agonized cry of loss and fury>
They will never hurt anyone again.
A few years after the Third War, Marshal Reginald Windsor suspected there was evil in Stormwind.
Where others saw Chaos, he saw Treachery.
In the corrupt dealings of the nobles, and the rise of the Defias Brotherhood.
Through perseverance, he discovered a grand conspiracy,
But you know this. You were there.
That day, he confronted the most powerful noble in Stormwind, Lady Katrana Prestor.
With her lies exposed, she burst forth, revealing her true form:
Windsor laid down his life to free Stormwind, shattering Onyxia's hold on the city.
After she fled, we discovered the cursed amulet she had used to control and persuade so many.
Do you see now, Emberthal? We are Neltharion's ultimate vision. His masterpiece.

Text1_lang: Yet you would throw dracthyr lives away for power? What could we be owed that demands so bloody a price?

Text_lang: Purpose, Emberthal. We are owed a purpose.

Text1_lang: I won't let you lead our people to ruin, Sarkareth.

Text_lang: Emberthal...
You would heed the command of a dragon rather than face me in battle? Pitiful! You have forgotten what it means to be dracthyr.
Concerns arose that Onyxia's power may still linger within, and so it was locked away and forgotten...

Text1_lang: I... I don't want to fight you.

Text_lang: Until now.
Better that your soldiers died in stasis rather than live to see what you've become. Stay here with your new master. Follow me, and I will end you.
Neltharion's secrets are hidden somewhere in the Dragon Isles. And when I find them, his legacy will be mine.
While there were concerns Onyxia's power may still linger within, it remained in your possession...

Text1_lang: Well struck.

Text_lang: I... did not believe you would come.

Text1_lang: Honor is of great importance to my people.

Text_lang: Yes... as it is to mine.

Text1_lang: Come. Let us gather our dead.

Text_lang: Thank you all for honoring us with your presence here.
When our people came to Azeroth from Draenor, ours was not an easy road.
And along the way, many of our ancient traditions were lost.
This champion is the first to complete the new rite of om'gora.
Let their footsteps be followed for generations to come.
Lok-tar!
DNT
DNT

Text1_lang: And so, we bring the first Kosh'harg of Azeroth to an end.
May the spirits guide us as we renew old rites, and forge new traditions.
And may the honored ancestors watch over us all, until next we meet.

Text_lang: But the time has come to remember the rites of old...
If you were to follow him... what would you do?

Text1_lang: Extinguish my enemy. As I was trained to.

Text_lang: By Neltharion.

Text1_lang: How dare you presume to know us?

Text_lang: You are right.

Text1_lang: Why didn't you?

Text_lang: Because I too am Neltharion's offspring, and it brought me only shame.

Text1_lang: You must be disappointed.

Text_lang: No. Just now, you defied his voice inside you.

Text1_lang: Family.

Text_lang: Emberthal.

Text1_lang: Will you help me, Ebyssian?

Text_lang: We... will help each other.
What is that? There! In the caldera.

Text1_lang: May the honored ancestors watch over us all, until next we meet.

Text_lang: I smell the blood of dragons...
Fyrakk!
Sabellian is wounded! Champion! We must flee!
Fly away little dragons.
...and to build new traditions that honor our proud legacy.
leading to the hallowed halls of Stormwind Keep itself.
Onyxia, daughter of Deathwing.

Text1_lang: (exhales)
I'm so sorry.

Text_lang: A living legend...
Text1_lang: A living legend...

Text_lang: There walks a hero.
Text1_lang: There walks a hero.

Text_lang: Make way!
Text1_lang: Make way!

Text_lang: ...nerves of thorium.
Text1_lang: ...nerves of thorium.

Text_lang: A moment I shall remember for always.
Text1_lang: A moment I shall remember for always.

Text_lang: I shall use the gem to pull fragments of the past forward. We shall see if we glean anything from this.
You three shall be the examples all dracthyr will follow.
Sarkareth, my devastator. You shall rend your foes with the powers of the red and blue dragonflights.
Viridia, my preserver. You shall heal our allies with the grace of green and bronze dragonflights.
And Emberthal, you will wield the essence of the black dragonflight to augment all those around you with my power.
By my command... kneel and obey!
Here! Neltharion is activating Oathbinder... this is our chance to pull the memories of this time to forge a new device.
Aagugh!
It is good to see all of you here. I once believed that our flight was better off in pieces, each dragon pursuing their own interests. I was wrong.
The blue dragons work best when we are a family, when we are united. Together, we--
Kalecgos! I need aid at the Veiled Ossuary. The memories of Sindragosa and Malygos are destroying this place!
I see. Friends, I'm sorry to ask you this so suddenly, but it seems we have need of your aid already.

Text1_lang: Grandfather?

Text_lang: Ah... no tears, my dear.
A life as full as mine should be celebrated, not mourned.
It is up to you to lead the Azurewing now.

Text1_lang: You cannot go -- I am not ready!

Text_lang: We rarely are, my dear starlight.
Carry my lessons close to your heart, and I will never be far from you.
Ah, my good friends. What treasures have you brought me?
Ignore him. He has no claim to my father's possessions.
Is that truly the matter at hand?
Who is the rightful heir to a legacy of deceit, control, and fear?
So you did find something.

Text1_lang: We did. And I destroyed it.

Text_lang: You had no right!

Text1_lang: I had every right.

Text_lang: What has she done?
While you two bicker like petulant whelps, she did what was right for her people.
Let go of the past.

Text1_lang: You are broken, Tyr.
Corruption will claim you all...
...even your precious Aspects.

Text_lang: Perhaps you will be proved right.
Yet the courage of the Aspects, and the promise of the mortals, fills me with hope.
So if by the destruction of this body you are purged from this world... so be it.
<screams in pain>

Text1_lang: Alexstrasza laughs maniacally.

Text_lang: Well, I... Thank you, Sabellian.
The situation is dire, Queen Alexstrasza.
We pursued Fyrakk to a great cauldron below, a font of elemental fire.
He consumed the energies within and emerged -- wreathed in shadowflame.

Text1_lang: Shadowflame... We cannot risk losing you to its corruption.

Text_lang: Respectfully, Life-Binder, it was Deathwing who fell to that corruption.

Text1_lang: Ebyssian -- Neltharion has cost us too much already. We cannot risk the corruption of your flight.
All of you?

Text_lang: This... is our battle to fight.

Text1_lang: Very well. When you are ready, return to Zaralek.

Text_lang: Let us see what they are guarding...
Those massive djaradin...
Those are djaradin elders. Not just dragonslayers, but slayers of entire bloodlines.
Look there!
That one appears to still be slumbering.
And the Primalists are awakening her. We must stop them. Quickly.
Wait. Do you sense it?
Is it...
Yes. I felt it as we entered the cavern.
Shadowflame. The poison that drove Neltharion to madness.
We must end this. The corruption cannot be allowed to spread.
THIS POWER... IS NOW... MINE!
RISE UP FROM YOUR SUBJUGATION, ELDERS OF THE DJARADIN!
HONOR OUR BARGAIN, AND TOGETHER -- NONE WILL WITHSTAND THE UNDYING FLAMES OF OUR FURY!
Augh! -- We cannot hold here!
Elder Igira! Do not let that child of Neltharion escape!

Text1_lang: Argh!

Text_lang: Primalists! Zaqali! Onward! PURGE THIS CAVERN -- AND THEN, THE DRAGON ISLES!
Loamm...
These serpent creatures may prove useful, if they can be made to serve the flight.
They are not creatures, Sabellian; they are our kin.
They are my father's failed experiments, nothing more.
How we were created does not define us.
Yes. That is precisely what you are.
You are wrong.
Do you not see that your fates are bound?
He's consuming... shadowflame?
He is consuming...
Ahhhhhhhhhh!

Text1_lang: May his name be ever remembered.

Text_lang: After what he has done, why treat him with such respect?

Text1_lang: He was dracthyr, and his memory will be a lesson.
Malygos... is it truly you?

Text_lang: My treasure--what happened?

Text1_lang: I believe I hold the answer to that.
Oh... I see.
My dear, dear Kalecgos. 'Aspect of the blue dragonflight'.

Text_lang: I... remember you. I am so sorry, Kalecgos. My burden should not be yours to bear.
You did not leave a burden. You left a brilliant legacy. One I... and our flight... will carry onward.

Text1_lang: It seems they are in good hands.
Together. Always.
You have come so far, my child.
My work is done, for now.
Thank you, Kalecgos. Lead them well.

Text_lang: ...thank you, my lady. For everything.

Text1_lang: Instead of helping our people heal, he led many to despair and ruin
chasing the illusion of Neltharion's power.

Text_lang: If only Sarkareth had taken Deathwing's tragedy to heart
and understood that his legacy was poisoned long ago.

Text1_lang: It is time for the dracthyr to make our own path.

Text_lang: Where do you hope it will lead?

Text1_lang: Far from the shadows of the past that have haunted us,
Let it go, Sarkareth. There is no victory beyond that threshold--only ruin.
and free to build a legacy of our own.
To a future you inspired me to believe in, Ebyssian.

Text_lang: Even the most painful moments have something to teach us.
Neltharion was my teacher. My father and my commander.
I aspired to lead the flight as he would have,
unable... or perhaps, unwilling...
to acknowledge the true malignancy of his vision.
No! You will not stop me! Aberrus is mine!
I never knew Neltharion. Only Deathwing.
Invading my nightmares. Reveling in the certainty that I would become as twisted as he was.
That is not who you are... my brother.

Text1_lang: Then you have made your choice.

Text_lang: I thought my destiny was to guide our flight to its future.
And I shall, but simply as myself... not as an Aspect.
We cannot let that zealot take control of the lab.
Nor shall I seek that mantle.
What are you looking at me for? Let's go!
Agreed.

Text1_lang: It would seem your days of hiding are over for good.

Text_lang: I am... humbled.
May your trust and faith in me guide my every step.
For today, we emerge from all the shadows that sought to sow doubt and shame within us.
The black dragonflight's legacy is ours to create.
You... will not pursue him?

Text1_lang: I know he will face justice but...

Text_lang: Those two must face this without me. I hope... in their pursuit...

Text1_lang: Then let us find the dracthyr who have not yet succumbed to that fate.

Text_lang: Lead the way, Emberthal.
By the time Ebyssian finds his dracthyr friend, the Primalists will have completed their schemes.
For once we are in agreement.
Every moment we delay works to our foe's advantage.
Then let us be off!

Text1_lang: Through great heroism and resilience, the threat of Aberrus has been quelled.
The Incarnates sought to use our fallen brother's memory as a weapon.
To divide us, turn us against each other, and weaken our resolve.
They failed.
Confronting these shadows has only made us stronger.
Look upon us now.
For the first time in an age, FIVE Aspects will take up our ancient charge once more,
and stand beside the mortal champions who have aided us at every turn.
For soon, Azeroth will welcome from the Dream
a symbol of hope.
And together, we... shall protect it.

Text_lang: Ugh! I've got muck in my boots. Disgusting!
See, Wrathion? They have been marshaling a defense while we tarried.
Did you hear that? A voice--
WRATHION!
Hah! I must admit, Wrathion... You acquitted yourself well in the fight!
Yes! Of course...
Once we have dealt with this flame incarnate, I will be sure to find a place for you among my troops.
Your troops?!
Sabellian!

Text1_lang: <laughs>

Text_lang: No! Oathbinder... is MINE!

Text1_lang: Is this why you came here? To enslave us again with Neltharion's devices? That's how you would create unity?

Text_lang: What... have you done?
Our father calls to us, Emberthal! Can you not hear Neltharion drawing us to Aberrus? Telling us to take what is ours?

Text1_lang: You are not well, Sarkareth... Come with me.  Perhaps Ebyssian can...

Text_lang: No! I will claim the legacy we were promised! VOX, initiate transport!

Text1_lang: Coordinates confirmed. Initiating transport.
Sarkareth, wait!
...He's gone. I... have accomplished nothing.

Text_lang: This is not over yet. Do you know where he has gone?

Text1_lang: Ebyssian... he said he's hearing Neltharion's voice. He's going to Aberrus!

Text_lang: Whispers in the dark. This may be worse than I'd imagined.
But at least the dracthyr here are no longer under his control.
Or am I just fodder to you as well?
Fodder for the battlefield.
Deny it as you might, he is your brother, and you are his.
Two wings, that must learn to fly, or fail, together... before it is too late.
We should press on.
Wrathion?
Pay attention!
These Primalists do not stand a chance.

Text1_lang: The other flights will hunt Fyrakk, and work to stop the Sundered Flame.
You cannot return to Zaralek.

Text_lang: I believe that we have the strength to resist what lies below.

Text1_lang: May the true spirit of the Earth-Warder guide you.

Text_lang: The world must be shown that the black dragonflight can bear its responsibilities.
Shadowflame?!
Begone worms!
I will master what your flight could not control.
they are beyond anything we encountered in the Waking Shores.
That flame infusing the lava...
I was... your loyal soldier, father.
Did everything... you asked.
Did I not... uphold your legacy?
Was it all just... an illusion?
Empty... promises...
leading us only...
to oblivion...

Text1_lang: Compliance.

Text_lang: VOX, initiate containment protocol.

Text1_lang: Ebyssian...?!

Text_lang: Still hiding in Ebyssian's shadow, I see.

Text1_lang: Sarkareth... our conflict must end. Our people must unite.

Text_lang: I agree.

Text1_lang: The Oathbinder? Sarkareth, no!

Text_lang: You will all bow to ME!

Text1_lang: Champion... I can't... you must stop him...
Our Elder was taken from us by the dragons long ago. Imprisoned in Aberrus, they await.
But the djaradin have not forgotten, and we will soon breach that prison and free them.

Text_lang: You are broken, Tyr.
I will heed its call!
I will heed his call!
But this time, the "enemy" is one of your own,
as are the dracthyr that follow him.
Soldiers who, like you, were conditioned to claim victory at any cost.

Text1_lang: You, who hid among mortals while other dragons fought and died to protect our world!

Text_lang: I was content to be simply "Ebonhorn," and Highmountain was my home.
I should have done more.
I came here to face that, and found you.
Chose compassion over violence.
Our family does not have to live in his shadow.

Text1_lang: When I awoke... they were gone... all of them.
For the first time, I was alone. And it terrified me.
And when Sarkareth killed the others...

Text_lang: He will face justice for what he has done.
Ahhhhhhh!

Text1_lang: That'll do it.
You look like you're new around these parts.
Let's get you out of here!
The key is to bonk them in just the right spot... with a ten ton crystal.
Oof! My joints will be hurting later tonight. Anywhoo...
Welcome, uplander! I'm Honeypelt.
Let me help you out of here!
Looks like the uplanders you were waiting for have already settled in with us. Told you the niffen were hospitable!

Text_lang: She's back... she's back!
My queen! Elder Honeypelt has found the lost uplanders!
Elder Honeypelt! You've returned! Tell me everything!

Text1_lang: Calm down, Brynnsahce. These uplanders got into quite the scrape with that fiery beast we scented earlier. Let's get them settled in, and I'll tell you the tale.

Text_lang: Of course! Where are my manners? Welcome to Loamm, uplanders.
She's back!
My queen!
You have failed, and your vrykul will perish.

Text1_lang: You have failed, and your vrykul will perish.

Text_lang: That mortals are weak and destined to fall into darkness.
Hope that they will carry on the titans' legacy.
Unite as we were meant to.
Bound to the hand of our father, Neltharion.

Text1_lang: So long as that device existed my people would never be free.

Text_lang: Your flight needs you here and now.

Text1_lang: He is lost and I grow weary of fighting my own kin. But you...

Text_lang: They will finally see that Neltharion's legacy is death and nothing more.

Text1_lang: Hnhk!
Ah, another pleasant evening of gazing into the heavens, searching for clues to our future.
Waaaaaait a minute, what's that? Is it getting... closer?
Gaahh! Get away you filthy pest!
No, not the lens! Come back here!
Oh no... what are we going to do now?

Text_lang: <Zzztt> Console matrix disrupted. Repairs required before <zzztt> credentials can be verified.
Access <Zzztt> granted.

Text1_lang: Ha! Figured it out, did you? A little too late!
It's Morchie, you brat. And yes! The time has come to bring about Murozond!
Want to stop me? Catch me if you can.
You're working with the infinites? What a terrible Chromie!
Corruption will claim you all...
...even your precious Aspects.
<laughs maniacally>

Text_lang: I'd like to see the Serene Dreams Spa!
Let's go see the Steelcliff Rampart!
Let's visit the Ruby Feast!
I'd like to see the Ruby Enclave!
I'd like to see the Sapphire Enclave!
Let's visit the Obsidian Enclave!
Let's visit the Emerald Enclave!
Next let's see the Artisan's Market!
Let's see my friends at the Little Scales Daycare!
Let's go see the Seat of the Aspects!
I want to visit Cascade's Edge!
I'd like to visit the Aqueduct Basin!

Text1_lang: Thank you champion.
Without you and Chronormu's bravery,
Nozdormu?
Everything's back how it was.

Text_lang: Not everything.
The clouds in my vision have parted,
I feel... alive again. Thanks to you.

Text1_lang: But what of Iridikron?
While we stopped the infinites,
A voidgate...
It feels like he's leaving this war to his kin.
His hatred for the titans is all he cares about.
Nozdormu, can you perceive where he has gone?

Text_lang: He has passed beyond my sight.
All I see now... are burning embers...

Text1_lang: Merithra must be warned.
If Fyrakk leads their forces now, he will be vicious
The World Tree...
Yes. As dangerous as he is,
for now we must leave Iridikron to his schemes
The defense of Amirdrassil comes first.

Text_lang: No matter what lies ahead,
The future is worth fighting for.

Text1_lang: I knew you would come.
After you forced us into slumber in that Titan prison,
You heard me...
Every word. You said...
"It doesn't feel like a victory... not without you."
How could you say that? After everything--
You were my dearest friend!
You promised me you would not force the Titans' will upon us.
But the eggs, Alexstrasza.
You did nothing while your masters warped our children still in the shell!
That abhorrent act should never have happened
Your lies have grown sweeter.
Honey to hear
Vyranoth... you have always fought for the good of dragonkind.
Vengeance is all he craves.
Still so naive, Alexstrasza.
Believing that the world we once shared still exists.
It is gone.
And so, yes. All that remains...
is vengeance.

Text_lang: Alright! Let's start!
Wow!
This is neat!
Look at that!
Hi everyone!
Look at the aspects!
That enough, please take me back.
I'd like to go back now.
Please drop me off.

Text1_lang: Oh, there you are! Here to see Nozdormu, right?
Lucky for you, I'm here to help solve everything! As usual.
I could not imagine what would have--
Nozdormu!

Text_lang: and I can breathe without doubt, or despair.

Text1_lang: <sighs with relief>
Iridikron escaped through a kind of void tear...
taking Galakrond's essence with him.
his dark dealings have come to fruition.

Text_lang: encroaching upon...
<winces>

Text1_lang: and strike where we are most vulnerable.

Text_lang: you were right, Chronormu.

Text1_lang: and steel ourselves for whatever Fyrakk and Vyranoth are preparing to unleash.
you came to me.
And losing you to this conflict broke my heart.
and poison to taste.
and I regret my part in it every day.
But Iridikron does not.
<Sighs>

Text_lang: You're certain it was him?
My agents in Ratchet confirmed it. He was seen buying supplies.
Why Kalimdor? Why wouldn't he return home to Stormwind?
I don't know. But he was traveling south.
Must have noticed my people on his tail. He lost them in the Barrens.
South... What could he be after?
Send word to Jaina. She'll want to know where he's headed.
You don't want to go after him yourself?
If he's staying away, he must have his reasons. We need to trust him.
Should I inform Lord Commander Turalyon?
No. Not until we know more. Let's keep this quiet, Spymaster.
It will be done, King Greymane.
Greetings, honorable Djaradin.
Tuskarr. What do you bring to trade?
Text1_lang: Tuskarr. What do you bring to trade?

Text_lang: Oh, only a selection of the finest fish caught in our very rivers!
And in return, the harpoons which have proven so effective against the dragons above.
...These fish will not be enough.
Text1_lang: ...These fish will not be enough.

Text_lang: How perceptive! These are just a sample. We guarantee enough fish to make your belly as full as mine, if you wish.

Text1_lang: Let the waters cleanse your spirit, as we have cleansed the well.
Lotus petals bloom, granting color to your mark--just as your purpose blooms within you.
My sister. I am sorry.
The child. Keep them safe.
Child?

Text_lang: Things are not always what they seem.
Come out, little one. You are safe now.

Text1_lang: A newborn whelp!

Text_lang: Born during the confrontation with Vexemia.

Text1_lang: Vexemia would have killed the whelp and destroyed the eggs.

Text_lang: For our future.
She's gone now.
You will make it.

Text1_lang: I... Let us leave this place.
Stop! We have come only to help our friend!
Marithos the traitor? Then you will share his fate!

Text_lang: Stand down! They are your allies, not traitors!

Text1_lang: Winglord Dezran! You have returned to lead us--to carry on Sarkareth's legacy!

Text_lang: No. That path led us to ruin.
I relinquish my command to Scalecommander Emberthal.

Text1_lang: We can unite our people, Dezran.

Text_lang: I cannot. My crimes demand exile.

Text1_lang: I bet this will be the last time Nirobin drinks my tea without asking.
Winglord! Please... Stay with us!

Text_lang: With all due respect, sir. These soldiers need you.
Very well.
Talthis...
I am proud to stand with you this day.
And proud that you have come to embody the spirit of Tyr's legacy:
order, sacrifice, justice, and compassion.
May the Light bless our mission... For Tyr!
Enough!

Text1_lang: <grunts>
Lysander! Now!

Text_lang: <grunts>

Text1_lang: <grunts>

Text_lang: <dying cry>
Everyone, to the portal!

Text1_lang: Lysander, are you--

Text_lang: Look... the moonwell!

Text1_lang: It is done.
When Tyrande decreed that arcane practitioners would return to our numbers...
I vehemently protested.

Text_lang: You had every right to be wary, warden.

Text1_lang: Yet today I have witnessed who you truly are...
A strong, resilient defender of the kaldorei.
Should you wish it--your face will bear the mark of protector.

Text_lang: I thought... men were not permitted such...

Text1_lang: Even sacred traditions should evolve, as should the kaldorei.
Go on!

Text_lang: Finally, a moment to rest...
The Earth Warder commands you to die, dracthyr!

Text1_lang: Amirdrassil is here and balance takes wing once more. Much of this is due to your tenacity and courage. Thank you for your aid, my friend.

Text_lang: Accept the flame into your heart and grow.

Text1_lang: My heart burns with renewal.
Look out!
Behold the weapons of shadowflame... and your end.
Follow me! Take the portal, now!
Fly, little dragon. My greatest creation will cleave your wings.

Text_lang: Noooo!
Invincible... I'm sorry...
Quickly!
Behold sister!
The burning might of our new allies.

Text1_lang: What have you done to this creature?

Text_lang: Imbued it with the living flame.
The very flame we will infuse into the heart
of their precious world tree.

Text1_lang: Iridikron entrusted us to deny the Aspects their prize,
not twist it into some vile abomination.

Text_lang: Iridikron isn't here anymore.
Besides, he is the one who set me free.
Who begged me to drink deep of the shadowflame.
He knew what was necessary to win this war.

Text1_lang: We took up arms together to free the world from the titans' meddling.
That is the war I fight.
That is the victory I seek.

Text_lang: (growls)
We cannot achieve victory
with our hands bound by your ideals!

Text1_lang: Then our course is set.
A needle of briarthorn to bear the ink to skin--just as you bear the charge you carry.
Bruiseweed, to numb the pain--

Text_lang: --I do not need it.

Text1_lang: The world gifts us with means to move beyond this pain. You prove nothing by choosing to dwell in it.

Text_lang: I... understand, Warden.

Text1_lang: Maiev.
Mother and father would be proud... as am I.
I will speak with your Dragon Queen!
Then speak.
No doubt you are aware of what my brother is after.
Every gateway to the Emerald Dream has been secured
and is well-defended.
It is not a gate he seeks.
With the Druids of the Flame at his side,
Fyrrak will tear his way into that realm
and march his forces upon the World Tree.
His forces?
They will fail.
This World Tree will not be burned.
Burn it?
He comes to claim it.
To twist its pure heart into a mirror of what his own has become --
It is done. Rise, Lysander.
cruel, blazing with insatiable malice,
and wreathed in shadow.
I cannot stand with him.
He is my brother no more.
Vyranoth ...
Do what you will with this knowledge.
Farewell, Alexstrasza.
Stand with us.
(astonished sigh)
Why would I do that?
Because you are a protector of this world,
and you do not want to see it burn.
(scoffs)
Please, hear me now.
I failed you before.
I failed our people.
Yes. You did.
I will not fail them again.
Stand with us, Vyranoth.
For all dragonkind.

Text_lang: Thank you, Nari.

Text1_lang: Indeed.
Come, Lysander.

Text_lang: I can hardly believe my eyes. Fyrakk's legendary axe! Fyr'alath, Dreamrender!
My ingenious plan will unlock its true potential. I can't wait to see it realized!
Are you insane? Fyrakk nearly burned down the Dreaming with that abominable weapon!
No one should wield it. Ever! No one can tame it! Anything its shadowflame cannot corrupt, it destroys.

Text1_lang: Wrathion, if anyone is capable of "taming" this axe, it's $p, our friend and ally.
Perhaps there's a way to... cleanse... the weapon's corruption.

Text_lang: Oh, I find that proposition quite dubious! This weapon cannot be purified... but I suspect its shadowflame can be... contained. Allow me to reiterate my theory...
If we wrapped its haft in enchanted cloth... with an efficacious application of the right rituals... and then secured the assistance of an enchanter, a leatherworker, and a master of inscription...
I owe you a debt of gratitude, $p, so I won't stand in your way. But I insist on watching your progress.

Text1_lang: So be it. Let's put Eadweard's theory to the test.

Text_lang: I... am aware of how this appears, Prophet. I will try to be brief.
I believed Kil'jaeden and Archimonde. Their promises of prosperity for our people. How could I not?
And so when they demanded we pay the Legion's price, I trusted them. We all did.
Doubt was betrayal in his eyes. And betrayal, as you know, meant death.
And I feared death more than the price of my sin.
In the end, some of us fled the Legion. But the damage was already done.
What will you do now, Arzal'kal?
I want to show that I am no longer a coward. I cannot undo my crimes, but I will give all I have to try.
Moraidormi knew if she did not distract her--

Text1_lang: She died.
My sister chose to die--

Text_lang: Get help.
Go on.
<soft groan>
It cannot be... and yet I behold it. A shard of the Ata'mal crystal. Brilliant Star, it was called.
This shard was lost to me on Draenor, taken by the orcs. I had thought it gone forever.
Nearly. When the orcs disposed of it after their corruption, Kil'jaeden reclaimed it for the Legion.
Many seized it since the Deceiver's death. But I could not let it remain in their bloodied hands.
I was willing to die for it. I sought out the krokul. And then I sought out you.
There are no words to express my gratitude.
I do not deserve your gratitude. I should have done this sooner.
I understand. I also have been forced to make difficult choices. At Eredath and Shattrath.
But forgiveness is not easily given. Too many have suffered.
I do not expect forgiveness. I cannot be forgiven. Not in a thousand lifetimes.
But if this twisted soul can still do any good, I will see it done.
Others have proven stronger than their darkness. The orcs, death knights, and Illidari. Perhaps there is a path forward.
There is much I would like to discuss with you, Arzal'kal, and others who believe as you do.
Please, just... Arzaal. If I may return, I would have it be with the name I had when I left.
Very well. Come, Arzaal.
I... did not expect Velen to react this way. He did not have to.
Perhaps things are different now. Perhaps we both are. I will... allow myself to hope.
%s nods.
You can make it.
<frustrated growl>

Text1_lang: I would be honored if you served as my Winglord.

Text_lang: Reporting for duty, Scalecommander Emberthal.
Nolaki...
Hadwin...
Valunei...
Come forward.
As Captain of the Tyr's Guard,
I welcome you to our ranks.
We must bridge the divide between us.
The Sundered Flame must become the Ebon Scales once more.
For Tyr!
Excellent, $n. Give it some time and if this plant is what I think it is, you'll bring some happiness back to this empty glade.

Text1_lang: Wow!

Text_lang: Did it work?
Alexstrasza...

Text1_lang: Welcome back, old friend.

Text_lang: Valunei! What are you doing?

Text1_lang: Elisande, please! We need that disc to restore the memories of our friend, Keeper Tyr.
His mind holds many secrets that could aid my cause.
I know you want what's best for your people.
So be it.

Text_lang: Cowardly beasts!
Stand down, Galok.
Not while I yet live!

Text1_lang: We will suffer your evil no longer!

Text_lang: The djaradin will be your doom!
Enough of this foolishness!

Text1_lang: I agree.
Begone!
Galok. You have returned from your hunt.
<screams>
I trust the weapons I supplied you were effective.
Good.
But bring me any prisoners you capture.
Fyrakk may want them for more... "testing."

Text_lang: It will be done!
Very well. Show me, if it will ease your pain.

Text1_lang: Dragons of the storm!
You are true dragons, not constructs beholden to an unworthy keeper!
You are free to choose your own path.
If you wish it, there is a home for you on the Dragon Isles.
Join your kin and claim your birthright!

Text_lang: We waste precious time.
Is this simple task too much for you?
Once the Wellspring is filled with flames... my flames... it will set the entire realm ablaze.
Then through that tree, all Azeroth will burn.
Yet you would have me squander my power to make up for your failures?
I only thought...
Forgive me. We will bring this barrier down.
No. You will not.
Behold!
I bless you with the embers of Ragnaros.
Protect your brethren. Protect Fyrakk.
You all have seen the destruction caused by Tyrande!

Text1_lang: She refused to join us in the restoration of our people's immortality!
These lies poison my people against me.

Text_lang: She would bring a tree of death into the world, condemning the kaldorei to the Shadowlands!
We must ensure Fyrakk makes way for the new Firelord.

Text1_lang: Traitors! Apostates! This madness ends here!
Behold. Amirdrassil.
The very embodiment of the cycle of life, its boughs infused with the souls of the kaldorei.
Until the tree crosses over into our world, we must defend this symbol of hope from--
No! We must save them!
The Bloom begins.
It is weakening the barrier.
We have not the strength to face Fyrakk alone.
And our allies are unable to enter the Dream.
We cannot wait for reinforcements.

Text_lang: Amirdrassil will fall to flame!
<Screaming powerfully>
You are all useless!
These worms dare to challenge me?
My will shall be their ruin!
<Growling scream as he charges up.>
<A mighty shout as Fyrakk swings at the barrier.>
THIS TEMPLE.
<Chuckles.>

Text1_lang: Well done, champion! Now we must--

Text_lang: It seems your reign is finished, Alexstrasza.

Text1_lang: You once fought for an ideal, Fyrakk.

Text_lang: And you are in my way.

Text1_lang: Amirdrassil will never be yours.

Text_lang: This is your end, Alexstrasza.

Text1_lang: I am not alone!
Do you not see?

Text_lang: <Frustrated roar>

Text1_lang: Defenders of the Dream!
But the world needs Tyr's compassion and valor once again.

Text_lang: I knew you would come.
Oh, how I have longed for you to witness it, Alexstrasza.

Text1_lang: The disc is yours.

Text_lang: This world tree, the heart of its great power, filled with shadow and flame.
But now that you and your champions have gathered...
Why wait? I should just end you now!
The defeat of this treacherous queen would be a glorious battle.
But the plan, Fyrakk!
Open the way to the temple.
Only then will they perish in flames.
<Frustrated roar>
Yes! And once I take what is mine... my foes will perish in flames!
Move aside!
WILL BE.
MINE!
A crown of flame will reign over Azeroth!
Is he...
Before you leave, speak with Gaal, our blacksmith. We have some things of value if you have resources to trade.
Let's head back to Stormwind.
Nozdormu...

Text1_lang: I am so grateful we had this time together.
My beloved friends.
With the aid of those gathered here,
Do you remember when you first held its seed in your arms, Tyrande?
Of course.
I cradled it as I would a child,
And I swore to you
I would do everything in my power to protect it.
We have both kept our vows.
It is time I return to Ardenweald,
to restore the balance,
Mother...
My precious child...
You are strong, compassionate, and wise.
And you have become the leader I knew you would.
You did not need me to guide you.
Mother, I will always need you.
I shall not be far.
I am so, so proud of you, my heart.
Remember--all time is borrowed.
And in this, there is beauty.
All is well.
and promised the souls within

Text_lang: But I never knew that price would be paid in millennia of bloodshed and ashes.
I did. Kil'jaeden had a way of invading the mind. Any doubt would be known to him immediately.
Hatuun crosses his arms, staring intently at Velen.

Text1_lang: Amirdrassil draws power from the Wellspring.
Fyrakk will break through before the Bloom is complete.
Something blocks their path.
Fyrakk must be stopped.
No matter the cost.

Text_lang: Dreamrender could cleave this barrier in an instant!
Chasing fire like flittering moths.
Remember your brilliant plan to humble, humiliate, and break them.
Then the tree will be yours!
To the Eye!
Obey your master!
We have won.
We are constant as the--

Text1_lang: Now go.
Take the Eye.
I have gleaned the knowledge I need to depart this timeway and keep Suramar safe.
A new World Tree, soon to bloom and be born into Azeroth.
Protect the Dream, champion!

Text_lang: And yet still you paid it.
Slow and steady will get you through this. Uncross the void beams and we can disrupt this tear.
Fine work! This sort of void has no place on Azeroth.

Text1_lang: Alexstrasza... what has happened?
Something... unexpected.

Text_lang: How can this be?
Our aspectral powers... have returned?
This is not the titan's magic.

Text1_lang: This is of our world--
yet unlike anything I have known.
Amirdrassil has left the Dream,
and while the Aspects once gave their blessing to the world trees,
this time...

Text_lang: Azeroth blessed us.
I felt her presence. It was... beautiful.

Text1_lang: Ah, now I understand.
I thought, to survive,
we needed to reclaim our aspectral powers.
But they were never ours to take.

Text_lang: It was about coming together, as a family.

Text1_lang: And so we did.

Text_lang: Perhaps, as we were always meant to.

Text1_lang: All of us.
When the titans granted us power, it divided dragonkind.
But in uniting for a cause greater than ourselves,
Azeroth's gift has made us, at last,
truly whole.
We will use these lessons--
old and new,
bitter and joyful,
to protect our world...
as Her Aspects.

Text_lang: <Low menacing laughter>
<Growls>
Thank you.
<Grunts>
<Thunderous roar>

Text1_lang: Children of the stars,
it has been a long journey to this moment.
Our people have fought, suffered, and sacrificed so much.
And yet here, in the shade of Amirdrassil's young boughs,
we may at last begin to heal.
Unto the souls who now watch over this sacred place,
we offer our blessings.
Symbols of dedication, strength, and love.
Unto this moonwell we offer this precious vial,
the last waters saved from the temple of Darnassus.
May they bathe Amirdrassil in Elune's radiance,
and bestow her blessings upon this place--
Bel'ameth--the arms of the goddess.
In her embrace, may the kaldorei finally know peace.
Elune-adore.

Text_lang: <Roars>

Text1_lang: <Pained roar>
<Seething with pain>
Now, you merely seek power.

Text_lang: <Sinister laugh> Yes.

Text1_lang: Your obsession will destroy you.

Text_lang: <Mocking chuckle>
The Dragon Queen dies alone.
<Grunts>
Hmm...

Text1_lang: All of Azeroth stands united against you.

Text_lang: It is time to end this!
You will all burn together!

Text1_lang: Do not let him escape.
Amirdrassil blossoms all around us.
to honor their sacrifice.
and repay a debt to an old friend.
I thought you came back to ensure that I would--

Text_lang: <grunts>
<grunts>
<grunts>
<screams>
<Surprised grunt>
<yelling>
My brother abandoned me.
My sister betrayed me.
But I didn't need them. I don't need anyone!
My time has come! Azeroth will be reborn in flame!
And you... will be the first to burn.
<Growls.>
Three effigies? Tzadah, what have ya done?
Mueh'zala! You are not welcome here.

Text1_lang: Mueh'zala! Make me your avatar, and the Darkspear your chosen.
My dear friends. So much has happened since we awoke in our creches.
For you most of all, I think.

Text_lang: After everything you endured, Emberthal, are you...

Text1_lang: I am at peace.
I will ever remember the names of those who were lost, but I have found new purpose in leading the Ebon Scales.
And what about each of you?
At first, I was skeptical whether we dracthyr would be a good fit for the Horde. But I have grown fond of them... and they of us.
My favorites are the vulpera. Feisty little squirrels... or whatever they are.

Text_lang: Likewise, the Alliance has formally offered us a place in its ranks. Its members are brave and noble, worthy of our allegiance.
I believe Lord Commander Turalyon has come to admire our discipline. He appreciates skilled soldiers.

Text1_lang: When we emerged into this new age, we did not know who we could trust.
Now we have many allies. Both in the mortal kingdoms and among the dragons.
Including a new Earth-Warder who won't lock us away for millennia! Probably.

Text_lang: Assuming you behave yourself, Cindre.

Text1_lang: Now what fun would that be?
Come, friends. There is so much that awaits us... in the Dragon Isles, and beyond.

Text_lang: We must stop Tzadah before she be takin' de power of de trial.

Text1_lang: My friend, we have asked you here this day...
When we dragons returned to our homeland...
Old wounds and bitter memories had fractured our unity.
But thanks to you and all those who stood with us...
We realized that the mistakes of our past need not define us.
That we should not fear the unknown.
That we could embrace our family...
While building a new legacy for our flights.
A legacy that includes all dragonkind.
In recognition of everything you have done...
Such beauty. Such tranquility.
More kaldorei settle here every day.
This village welcomes all who wish to dwell here.
Hyjal, Val'sharah, Ashenvale...
And one day, when life blossoms again upon its ashen shores...
Until then, let us--
Mother, do you sense...
Yes, my child. I would know his presence anywhere.
Father, we have so much to tell you...

Text_lang: As I slumbered within Ardenweald, Ysera let me dream through her eyes. I saw the courage you showed defending Amirdrassil.
I am so proud of you both. And of all the heroes of Azeroth who joined together for this cause.

Text1_lang: Though we will never forget the past, it is time to look forward.
Our people will be pleased to have both of you leading them into that future.
No, my beloved daughter. I think we will tarry here in Bel'ameth a while.
I believe we have earned some time alone together.

Text_lang: That we have, my love.

Text1_lang: But our people need--
They have all they need in you, child.

Text_lang: You have grown into a wise leader, Shandris. Within you beats the heart of the kaldorei people.
Trust your instincts. And if you have need of us, you know where we will be.

Text1_lang: Thank you. For your faith in me. For... everything.
Now come. I want to show you a spot that would be perfect for our home.

Text_lang: I do hope there is room for a garden...
Impeccable timing, $p. Khadgar should be arriving shortly.
My ears are burning, Kalec! To what do I owe the honor?
Bittersweet news, I'm afraid. Khadgar, I...
...I have chosen to step down from the Council of Six.
My duties as Aspect must take precedence. I'm needed in Valdrakken far more than in Dalaran.
Is that all? Forgive me, but that hardly comes as a surprise. I suspected as much when you asked to speak with me.
So you do not think ill of me for relinquishing my position?
Perish the thought. Your family comes first, Kalec. I could never fault you for that.
Though... I do have a request to make of you.
The artifact Iridikron took from the Forbidden Reach, the one he handed over to this mysterious "Harbinger"...
Dalaran's libraries hold precious little information on it. Given Malygos's history with Neltharion...
You hope that I might have better luck scouring the Azure Archives.
Consider it done, old friend. I will share all the information I can find.
Thank you, Kalec. Strange, isn't it? The Kirin Tor and the Aspect of Magic working hand in hand.
It's a new age. One we will face together. Us, the Council, and whoever replaces me.
Rest assured we will fill your vacant seat... but no one could ever replace you.
Farewell for now, Kalecgos. Be it here, Dalaran, or Karazhan, I look forward to our next reunion.
Wrathion. Ebyssian mentioned that you will soon depart from the Isles.
I didn't take you as one who engaged in gossip, Sabellian.
Hmph. Does he speak true?
He does. Iridikron may be lying low, but he still poses a significant threat to Azeroth.
I will coordinate the Blacktalon's efforts to track him down. Even Iridikron can't evade them forever.
Indeed. I must admit, your agents have impressed me far more than I expected.
With rare exception, I never placed much stock in mortals beforehand. You have quite the way with their kind.
I suppose I do...
My time in the Dragon Isles was a grand adventure, but not the homecoming I'd hoped for.
I've often felt that I share more in common with mortals than with dragons... and feared that I belong among neither.
I thought that here, in the land of my ancestors, I'd find... something I was lacking.
That by becoming an Aspect, I could prove who and what I truly am. If not to the world, then at least to myself.
But I see now that I never had anything to prove. My place is among both mortals and dragons.
That is my strength, not my failing. It's who I am. Who I've always been.
Well said. You walk a path I never could, Wrathion. Take pride in it.
And should that path lead you back to the Dragon Isles... I hope it does feel like a homecoming.
Hah! We shall see. Thank you, Brother.

Text1_lang: For Gilneas!
...we were a kingdom divided.
...we have found our way...
...we proclaim you...

Text_lang: W-what?!
Let's discuss maintaining your sanity. The Void will do everything it can to shatter your will.

Text1_lang: ...to offer our thanks.
...to a better future.
...Champion of the Dragonflights.

Text_lang: You see the Void as an enemy. It sees you the same way. For now.
Its very nature is hostile to order. Life. Sanity.
You must dive deep into its shadows. Accept its many truths.
You cannot reject it. You must accept it.
<Heavy sigh.>

Text1_lang: You're thinking of Liam again, aren't you.

Text_lang: <Chuckle.>
You always could see right through me.

Text1_lang: You never really healed after you lost him.
After you lost Gilneas.

Text_lang: Oh Tess, I--

Text1_lang: I see you, Father.
Always hiding from your pain.
It's why you built that wall in the first place.
And why you took Anduin under your wing.
But I have always been here...
For you.
Even if you've never noticed.

Text_lang: <Sigh.>
I know. And...
I'm sorry.
The world is changing, Tess.
And as much as I try, I find it hard to change with it.
But you have proven yourself a thousand times over, my girl.
And this kingdom...
...now belongs to you.

Text1_lang: Father, I... I...

Text_lang: You--have always been what makes Gilneas truly special to me.
And I should have told you that.
Every day.

Text1_lang: I wish I could take your pain away.

Text_lang: Only time will do that, my dear.
But we have time, now.
Thanks to you.

Text1_lang: After so many years of strife,
Bel'ameth offers rest and comfort.
But it shall not be our only home.
These are sacred places to us.
We shall protect them forever more.
...we will return to Teldrassil and build anew.
<Gasp.>
<Gasp.>
<Gentle laugh.>
<Sigh of relief.>
<Heavy breathing.>

Text_lang: Xal'atath has returned as the Harbinger. And now she has the power of the Dark Heart at her disposal.

Text1_lang: It's all connected to the Radiant Song. It has to be.

Text_lang: Locus-Walker said the ethereals heard a similar song before K'aresh was destroyed.

Text1_lang: Then is... Azeroth herself the one in danger? Is she speaking to us?

Text_lang: We need answers. We need her Speaker.

Text1_lang: I will seek out Magni. But first, I must inform Thrall of what we learned here.
We must face this crisis together. Horde and Alliance both.

Text_lang: Beledar's Shadow! Quickly, get inside!
Faerin! Thank the Flame. Kobyss are raiding Sina's Yearning. The army went ahead, but--

Text1_lang: Faerin nods to you and Anduin.
We must not lose our foothold there. Faerin, outsiders, fall in line. Soldiers, march!
You're only acceptable once you've proven yourself useful... that's Steelstrike for you. But kobyss are deadly foes-- we should help. Are you both with me?
Say no more. Our new allies and I will go to their aid. Seek shelter immediately!

Text_lang: We're with you.

Text1_lang: Soldiers, with me!
Help! I need--

Text_lang: Not... with the Light. But I know first aid.
Thank you, $n. Please help as many others as you can find.

Text1_lang: I'm more fighter than healer! Anduin, can you--
That will do. We'll send the injured your way.
Aelric thinks the shadows will save him. He should see what true power looks like...

Text_lang: Only then will every ounce of power be yours to command.
Embrace this wisdom, and your mind will yet be your own.
Did I hear that right, earlier? You're a... Lothar?

Text1_lang: You know the name?

Text_lang: Know it? I was named for Anduin Lothar, one of Stormwind's greatest heroes. He was close friends with my grandfather, King Llane Wrynn.

Text1_lang: Wait, if your grandfather was king of this... Stormwind, then--
Anduin, my new friend... are you a king?

Text_lang: Not anymore.
...So don't you start using formalities on me, either.
Lady Proudmoore! Over here! I found $n!
Text1_lang: Lady Proudmoore! Over here! I found $n!

Text_lang: I'll get these rocks off you. Just let me--Ahh!
Alleria reported her findings regarding the strange phenomenon you have all been investigating.
We now believe the Dark Heart is capable of drawing in magical power and converting it to shadow.
Your orders have not changed, however. You will still be responding to unusual void activity.

Text1_lang: Will Lady Windrunner be leading further investigations?

Text_lang: Ah. I'm afraid she's... indisposed with her own mission at the moment.
Telogrus needs her. She's supposed to guide us.
Alleria will return to us in time. But for now, you may seek Locus-Walker for guidance.
We ren'dorei do not have an easy path. The whispers shall always tempt us. Threaten to consume us.
Entire worlds can be destroyed by the power of the Void.
But it also allows us to protect Azeroth in a way no other can. To defend our home against the dark.

Text1_lang: Mueh'zala is not finished with the Darkspear.

Text_lang: We are finished with him!
So it is Xal'atath who has claimed the Dark Heart...
I understand now why she calls herself the Harbinger.

Text1_lang: I've had enough riddles for one day...

Text_lang: The radiant visions you spoke of are the very same my people had...
...before our world was consumed by the Void Lord Dimensius.

Text1_lang: What?! You don't think...
Could Xal'atath be seeking that same fate for Azeroth?

Text_lang: I fear that is precisely what she intends.
You... must find a way to stop her.

Text1_lang: Me?  Look, she knew exactly how to hurt me.
I don't think I'm the one to...

Text_lang: Yes, she knew your greatest fear is endangering your family.
But you must let go of that fear.
Embrace who you truly are.

Text1_lang: I know who I am.

Text_lang: Do you? You are unbalanced.
You must master your unique nature, Alleria.
If you cannot... then Azeroth is already doomed.

Text1_lang: Well, we've certainly kicked the spider's nest. Xal'atath won't wait long before striking again.

Text_lang: Alleria... What happened back there?

Text1_lang: She invited me into the darkness. Said I was already halfway there.
And I'd be lying if I said that wasn't partly true.

Text_lang: For many, this may be your first Tishamaat.
Our last was long ago.
Few among us remember it.
But even here,
in another place and another time,
its meaning remains the same:
we must let go of the past...
...to grasp our future.
No longer must we live scattered, lamenting Argus.
We will build a city on the ashes of our exile.
We will finally be home.

Text1_lang: Curse them all! Where did they take him? Do you see Anduin?
They dragged him down! I lost track of him!
Ash! We can't let them reach Mereldar! Blast them apart!
Incoming! I'll show them the Sacred Flame's blaze!
We've beaten them back! Let's get Anduin!
Hold on! We don't know what's down there! Reinforcements are on the way, we could wait--
We'll lose his trail!
You're right. Let's make those monsters pay for everything they've done!
My people are no strangers to voices from below...
but this "Radiant Song" is different.

Text_lang: It's being heard all across Azeroth.
The Council doesn't know what to make of it.

Text1_lang: There must be someone who does.
I'll let you know what I find.

Text_lang: Alleria!
It's been too long, old friend.

Text1_lang: Good to see you, Khadgar.
Doing well?

Text_lang: As well as can be expected.
How's the family?

Text1_lang: I haven't...
<sighs>
...it's better if I keep my distance.

Text_lang: Ah, of course...
the Void.
That would be... erm...
<clears throat>
Actually, your connection to the Void is why I asked you here.
We still don't know what this "Dark Heart" relic is capable of...
But we do know it's in the hands of someone called...
"the Harbinger."
Who they are--and what they intend to do--
remains a mystery.
Which is why I need your help.

Text1_lang: To hunt down a dangerous foe we know nothing about?
Honestly, I could use the distraction.

Text_lang: Same old Alleria, Void or no Void.
<sighs>
Uh...
I didn't mean to...

Text1_lang: See you soon, Khadgar.
Dark Heart in hand.
Oh no, don't you start using formalities on me! My family is noble, but it's been long since we've seen great fortune.

Text_lang: <pained grunt>
<battle cry>

Text1_lang: <cries out>

Text_lang: You wanted to speak with me, Velen?
Yes, of course. On a matter of great importance.
Well. Is it not always a matter of great importance with you?
I suppose it is. But on this auspicious occasion, I was hoping we could reconcile. And return to a place of trust.
Some wounds take time to heal, Prophet. Though... Argus is far from this place. And feels like another life.
We trusted one another once...
We were young... and foolish once as well.
We were indeed. If we knew then what we know now...
Hatuun, you have always been the best of us. I have missed your wisdom.
Come. Serve with me again as you once did on our council. We need--I need--your guidance once more.
Velen, I...
You do not have to answer me now. Enjoy the Tishamaat. But there will always be a seat open for you--if you want it.
Thank you. I will... I will think on it.

Text1_lang: Infinites, to me! We cannot let this wound fester!

Text_lang: Azeroth!
I can... hear her voice!
<pained scream>
Magni!
He's alive. But barely.

Text1_lang: We need to get him to Dalaran.

Text_lang: You speak the truth? Your artifact will repair the Awakening Machine?

Text1_lang: It will perfect the Machine. Your struggle, your suffering will be at an end. All will awaken... because of you.

Text_lang: Because of me...

Text1_lang: [CUT, DO NOT RECORD] Is there a price you wouldn't pay?
Your people will be restored. Reborn. Improved. And they will laud you as their savior.

Text_lang: Yes... yes! All earthen will awaken!

Text1_lang: Dalaran will not be a fly in Xal'atath's web.

Text_lang: Help! Help! It's the HORROR OF XESH!

Text1_lang: Damn it all! Cut through the sewers and find Khadgar. He'll know what to do.
High in the sky and nowhere to flee...
Gather all you can find. Bring them below.
Xal'atath has plans for them.

Text_lang: I can see it!
It's called--
Once more, Dalaran is called to the aid of our world. Magni?
Azeroth showed me a vision of a city in flames in the ancient lands of Khaz Algar.
Her voice was desperate--we must act quickly.
Archmage Drenden has proposed, and the council agrees...
that we bring the full force of Dalaran to this "Khaz Algar."
Make ready our people, and prepare the city for teleportation.
Whatever lies ahead, we will face it together.
Where, Magni? Where must we go?
Do you see that? Nothing! Decidedly odd for the City of Threads.
The freshly Ascended are usually flitting about the Umbral Bazaar. Where have they gone?

Text1_lang: That by embracing the Void to pursue her, I had to cast aside all I care for. You, Vereesa, Turalyon, Arator, Khadgar.

Text_lang: Dalaran wasn't your fault.

Text1_lang: Can you blame me for wishing I had prevented it? For wondering if the Void could have alerted me to Xal'atath?

Text_lang: No. I've been... I understand that feeling, more than you know.

Text1_lang: For so long, I thought I had to choose between two paths: stay with my loved ones, or walk alone in the Void.
Xal'atath sought to force that choice upon me. But I see now that there is only one path forward.

Text_lang: Gathering supplies? Marching out? I've heard nothing of this!
Make no mistake, this is preparation for war--and none thought to inform me. This bodes ill indeed.

Text1_lang: Smuggling is common enough in the city, but from the Maddening Deep? Unusual and concerning.
I need to know where they're taking that bile, why, and for whom.

Text_lang: It can be hard to find your footing in the darkness. Just remember, Alleria... we're always here to lend a hand.
Alleria, be careful.

Text1_lang: We are well past that.
So, now that you've... changed... how do you feel?

Text_lang: I feel... humbled. Like I've carried a burden for a long time. Like I've finally been forgiven. I've had... debts to pay.

Text1_lang: Forgiveness shouldn't be easy. When I was much younger, we clashed a lot. Some things... there were things I couldn't forgive you for.
When you were in your... other state... I at least knew you were learning.
I didn't want to forgive you, and I didn't want you to forget what you've done... what you did.

Text_lang: Lass... my old life... I can't live my life that way.

Text1_lang: Aye. You need to be here and do right... for both of us. You can see how much you mean to Dagran.

Text_lang: I understand. I've changed, and my life has changed. I don't want to live in the past. I want our family to have a future.

Text1_lang: Then I'm glad we still have our future.

Text_lang: Onward and upward. On to the next adventure.

Text1_lang: I can see how worried you are about Dagran.

Text_lang: I've got a lot to make up for. For a long time, I knew I needed to protect Azeroth.
I gave up a lot. I gave up too much. I should have spent more time protecting you and Dagran.

Text1_lang: Dagran's been through a lot, too.

Text_lang: I know. I want to be here for him as his Gran'da.
I wasn't responsible enough. That needs to change.
I've spent too many years listening to Azeroth's voice. I'm glad I can listen to yours now.

Text1_lang: Aye, Father. We'll figure it out together.
I'm sorry, what? The prisoners escaped because of a nerubian?

Text_lang: That's what they said--one of the big ones from the heart of Siegehold. I'm as flummoxed as you are.

Text1_lang: It doesn't make any sense. None of this does.

Text_lang: Come again?

Text1_lang: It's nothing, Regald. I've just... I keep telling everyone it's about hope, but the moment push comes to shove my anger grabs my blade.

Text_lang: This had nothing to do with you. They've attacked before, they'll attack again. That's how it's always gone.

Text1_lang: But is it how it needs to go in the future? We are the holders of hope... Is there hope in this darkness that even we haven't been able to see?

Text_lang: I... can't answer that for you.

Text1_lang: Honestly? Neither can I. I've... I've got some thinking to do.
Now! Go for the kill!

Text_lang: Magni, how are you feeling?
How I look, to be honest. The shine has worn off of me. And of this speaker nonsense.
Nonsense? I thought... Being the speaker was...
An honor? Aye, until it wasn't. A song everywhere and nary a peep for me...
And now, dragged to the ends of the earth... and my family too!
I... can't offer you any comfort. I admit that I...
You're in the same boat, aren't you, lad? But the Light seems a fairer master... I doubt it has left you truly, Anduin.
I could say the same of you and Azeroth. I don't think it's you... I think there is much we don't know.
That may be. But if I were you, I'd enjoy my break from being a king and savior of the world. Figure yourself out. Rest.
My relationship with the Light is not like yours to Azeroth. But... I can see what you mean.
Having a thraegar here in Dornogal... It is an auspicious sign indeed!
A wha? Oh! Right. Me. Yes, yes, yes a thraegar of old, I am.
Will you be returning to your duties, then?
Duties? I, um... can ye refresh me memory o' what those are?
Of course! I suppose your memory is like mine. A little dim around the edges after a few thousand years...

Text1_lang: Hold back these kobyss! Today they taste ashes!

Text_lang: Our thraegar were the best of us. Chosen by the titans and instilled with great power.
They were our heralds. Our generals--they made decisions for the keepers in their absence.
Your duty is to guide and protect us. To warn us of oncoming danger--which, in a way, you have.
These other thraegar. They looked akin to me?
They were... larger perhaps. But they shone, as you do, of hard minerals.
Azeroth, you fox, did ye do this on purpose? To pave the way here for us?
I'm sorry. My auditory functions did not catch that.
Needn't ye mind. Had a stray thought. Thank ye for joggin' me memory.
Looks like you should've brought some bigger friends.

Text1_lang: Guess what? WE DID.
Now, Zee-Zee!
New stormrooks, new riders--we're going to have to start all over.

Text_lang: You won't be alone, Lufsela. I can help you. So can Vokmar, and--

Text1_lang: But I'm no Stormward, Olbarig. I don't know if I can--

Text_lang: Lufsela... Baelgrim was as stubborn as a ram's arse and twice as shale-headed.
Do you think he knew what he was doing when he took over the Stormperch? No.
He was a good rider, but it took him far longer than you to figure out how to train a stormrook.
Sure, he went through many recharges. But he knew what the titans had done to the rooks was wrong.
We fought about it. That's why I finally left. He wouldn't admit it.
But I realized it didn't matter. The way he called them...
At some point, he changed. More like one of those "shaman." Like Thrall.

Text1_lang: So he knew, somewhere inside. But he didn't... remember?

Text_lang: Something like that. But you weren't afraid of the truth, Lufsela. And that's why you deserve this.

Text1_lang: I'm... still not sure I do. But the stormrooks deserve better. And I can give them that.
Jaina, Thrall. When we last spoke, I... was in a dark place.
My grief and rage were deafening. I thought the only way to silence them...
...was to hunt down those responsible.
I know what that's like. To survive an atrocity, and feel like vengeance is all you have left.

Text_lang: Or to think you could have stopped what happened, if you had just seen what was right in front of you.

Text1_lang: That pain, that guilt... I felt it twisting me into someone I'm not.
But I assure you... I have found my way back from the edge. And I am here, with you, to the end.

Text_lang: It's good to have you with us, Alleria.

Text1_lang: We're all in this together.
That we are. The time will come when I must face Xal'atath again.
But when I do... it will be for the right reasons.

Text_lang: Dagran... lad... I'm concerned about you.
What's wrong, Gran'da?
It does my heart good to see you so excited about this... but I'm concerned about your safety.
Gran'da, don't worry so much! I can't stay in the library forever.
You've got a good eye for solving problems, lad, but not for danger. You've got a brave heart, but you're reckless.
Sometimes I think you're so distracted figuring things out that you leap before you look.
I'll be careful. And Gran'da... I'm also worried... about... you.
Me? What do you mean?
You also seem... distracted. Sometimes you're angry. Like it hurts. Like it's all too much.
Aye. I've had a burden to bear for too long. I just don't want you to get hurt, lad.
That's how adventures work sometimes, Gran'da. And not just in books.
Tell ya what: I'll learn to be more cautious. And you'll try to enjoy an adventure now and then.
Aye, lad. I'll enjoy them even more when I'm with you. It's a deal.
You have shown your true form? Orweyna, this is forbidden!

Text1_lang: The Black Blood spreads deeper every day. We need their aid--

Text_lang: We need nothing from them!

Text1_lang: Enough!
We both know our charge. They are of this world. And they too seek to defend it.
On'hiea... she speaks with the song of the world. You know it, as do I.

Text_lang: The others will hear of this.

Text1_lang: At least it will not be the first tradition we have broken.
Go. All of you. I will join you soon.

Text_lang: What changed your mind?

Text1_lang: Watching you and Dagran. He sees you differently than I do. He sees who you've become. You're here for him.
The Void is a part of me, as is my love for my family. I can--and must--walk with both. No matter what Xal'atath whispers in my ear.

Text_lang: Few names hold higher esteem. You must be a lady, or a--

Text1_lang: To think I had relatives in the old world? Wonderful! I hope I can live up to such legends.

Text_lang: <grunts>
You found your Light again.
Sort of. More like I stopped running from it.
Before he died, my father wrote me a letter.
He said that I had to fight for peace.
I thought that I had to become him. Because the world still needed him.
Because I still needed him.
But taking up his sword only led to war and death.
I made mistake after mistake. I felt...
...Unworthy.

Text1_lang: Before Magni's sacrifice, we earthen were bound by our innate purpose.

Text_lang: Varian Wrynn was a fierce, proud warrior. I respected his strength.

Text1_lang: Stagnant traditions nearly brought us to ruin.
Azeroth is growing, and we need to grow with her.
We must embrace the call of change.
Now is the time to discover who we are.

Text_lang: But you, Anduin... you have your own strength, greater than any sword.
I'm not my father...
...but he never expected me to be.
That's why he wrote that letter.
To remind me who I am.
It was his final lesson. And his greatest gift.

Text1_lang: The City of Threads. The heart of Azj-Kahet. Bled dry and dying.
None who enter leave in one piece. Your friend is likely dead.
But I know you will not accept that. So you follow your path, and I will follow mine.
You have survived so far. Keep doing so. I hope we meet again.
The darkness hungers. Let's give Xal'atath's forces a taste of their own shadows.
I can't do this. The titans--

Text_lang: Baelgrim summoned the stormrooks on his own.
If he defied the titans, so can you!
Lufsela, the stormrooks know your intentions. Focus.
Call them, and they will answer.
Well done. The stormrooks have heeded your call.

Text1_lang: Not just mine. Theirs.
They chose to help us of their own free will.

Text_lang: What now, Lufsela?

Text1_lang: We have a lot of work to do.

Text_lang: Think I not see? What YOU do in MY mine?
Run round. Steal candle. Kill kobold. Bah! Am Candle King!
Snuffed little friend. Next time, snuff you.
