Snootsnout! Leave new friends e-le-men-tal present. And close door behind. We not entertain today.
We cannae hold 'em!
Stormriders!
To ground, my soldiers!
Trespassers. My directive is to protect the Isle of Dorn.
Leave at once.

Text1_lang: Trespassers? You saw us fall from the sky an' fight for our lives!
We need aid!

Text_lang: What you need matters not.
Your presence is not authorized by the titans.
The titans?
Now don't ye be talkin' to me daughter like that, ye great stone--
An earthen hardened like a diamond--a thraegar!
You've... seen others akin to me?
I have only heard stories of their heroics... It is a sign from the titans!

Text1_lang: Er, what he means to say is... Yes, of course! And we'd be honored to...

Text_lang: Dornogal! What disaster have you brought to our city, outlanders?

Text1_lang: The fuses! We can't ignite the kegs!

Text_lang: I must fulfill my edict.

Text1_lang: What? Forget the Edicts!

Text_lang: I cannot. That is why it must be me. You must guide the earthen.
One last ride. Then you are free.
Zirix!
<Hissing>
My directive is to protect this isle--and the earthen. All the earthen.
You must be eliminated.
Glory to the titans! Long live the earthen!
So... we are in agreement?

Text1_lang: Yes. We must assist our new allies.
And to do that we must renounce the edicts--forever.

Text_lang: It is fitting then, that we do so here--where it all began...
Where the Edicts were written.
Who would like to do the honors?
I, the Councilward of Dornogal, declare that we are all...
Unbound!
[DNT] Kahet iz korvan.
Text1_lang: [DNT] Kahet iz korvan.
...and apologies for the delay.

Text_lang: Lok'tar, everyone.

Text1_lang: How could I be so blind?
The dawntower! What is happening to it?
Aelric! She's-

Text_lang: The Harbinger has whispered to me of your arrival...
And your failure at Dalaran.

Text1_lang: Where is your master?

Text_lang: [Creepy laugh]
OUTLANDERS!
And who is this? Brinthe?
I have been busy addressing our greatest problem:
What distractions have you brought before me this time, Brinthe?
I have no time for your misadventures.
Enough!
The High Speaker... has SPOKEN.

Text1_lang: The High Speaker has ruled for as long as any of us can remember... but he's no longer one of us.
Well, sounds like you need a new High Speaker. And Brinthe, you're the right earthen for the job.
Me? Elaborate.
[CUT, DO NOT RECORD] Aye. You. No one's worked harder. No one's waited longer.
You cared for your people like no one else has. Not by commanding, but by understanding.
Then you know I will leave it to my people to decide.
Something tells me they already have.
Honor Guard, reporting for duty... if you'll accept the position...
I... accept. I am the High Speaker.
Personal directive: prioritize the wounded.
Unidentified. Another survivor from the crash?
I'm Moira, of the Dark Iron and Bronzebeard--
Baelgrim.

Text_lang: Stoneward.

Text1_lang: I am NOT the Stoneward. You know that.

Text_lang: I know you abandoned your post.

Text1_lang: And you abandoned us.

Text_lang: The Coreway was attacked!

Text1_lang: We were attacked too!
<clears her throat>
I can see there is some... history between ye.
But if ye haven't noticed...
Ye need each other, age-old drama or not.
These outlanders crashed on our shores...
High Speaker, the nerubians...

Text_lang: My orders were clear. And yet, more overcrawlers regularly slip from our grasp.
Failure! Unacceptable! Not only does this shame you, it shames me.
Which means no one will hear of it.
Clean up this refuse and get it out of my sight.
And if you breathe a word of this to anyone, you're next.

Text1_lang: We cannot fight if...

Text_lang: It must be repaired!

Text1_lang: You should have protected--
The nerubians have ye both in their sights.
Your Ascension...
Is complete.
Flames... they were ready for us.
Brace yourselves!

Text_lang: These earthen. They're a funny lot. Odd traditions. Superstitions.
What... do you mean?
She's melting me, I--!
Oh, you know, Titans,  Edicts... Thraegar...
Some of them have been calling me Arathi. Like the ancient human empire. I... wonder how they know of it.
Aye. I heard that too.
But it seems like the Arathi were here--recently. Why would the earthen have an inn with proper food and beds if they don't need them?
Do ye think the Arathi are here somewhere in Khaz Algar?
I don't see how. But... it bears investigating.
New directive: we must return to the city. All of us.
Laddie, it weren't titan magic tha--
I don't know what to make o' it. The earthen are also an ancient people. They might be just rememberin' ghosts.

Text1_lang: Well done! Now let's regroup ahead.
Baelgrim!
<grunts>

Text_lang: Deviants!
<bellows>
Must.. get away!
Speak to me.
The place she's calling us to...
Alleria. I heard you helped corner Zirix at the Meadery. Thank you.

Text1_lang: The nerubians took so much from us. I will not let them do the same to the earthen.

Text_lang: They've been good allies... and gracious hosts.

Text1_lang: A welcome surprise, given that they've been living in isolation for thousands of years.

Text_lang: That may not be entirely the case.
I asked about why they keep calling me "Arathi"... and apparently an Arathi armada arrived on Khaz Algar a number of years ago.
They're said to have formed a settlement in the caverns beneath the island. It sounds impossible...
But if it's true, I want to see it for myself. They could prove to be allies in our fight against Xal'atath.

Text1_lang: No. We've secured a measure of safety here. Don't abandon it to chase shadows in the dark.

Text_lang: Isn't that what you're doing?

Text1_lang: I'm doing what I must. Hunting down every last nerubian. Following their trail back to Xal'atath. And claiming vengeance for our dead.

Text_lang: I'm sorry, I didn't mean to--

Text1_lang: Remain in Dornogal, Anduin. Leave the shadows to me.
We have to get out of here now!
...Where's Anduin?
Anduin!

Text_lang: The Light will return...
Even if someone else carries the torch.

Text1_lang: Anduin!

Text_lang: <aggressive yell>

Text1_lang: No!
Out! Now!
She seized Y'tekhi's mind without even blinking.
If she can do that to one Ascended...

Text_lang: Light be my...
<breathing heavily>
<roars in rage, swings his sword with fervor multiple times>
<battle yells>

Text1_lang: <laughing delightedly>
Oh... please.
<painful cry>
I've seen you, Windrunner...
Always alone,
pushing everyone away to embrace the hunt.
Just like the monster you pretend not to be.
You're the only monster here.
Am I?
You've slain hundreds to find me.
Was that really all for Khadgar?
Or is it just your nature to destroy?
Come Alleria.
Embrace who you truly are.

Text_lang: Alleria.
Alleria.
Alleria.
Alleria.
Alleria!

Text1_lang: I know who I am.
<grunts aggressively>
<chuckles with amusement>
Run all you like.
I'm coming for all of you.
Join me. Please.

Text_lang: <scoffs defensively>
You know the Light is not with me.

Text1_lang: There is no darkness so deep that the Light cannot reach us.
Just be here. With me.
Now.
Breathe.
<audible breaths>

Text_lang: <audible breaths>

Text1_lang: We are the seekers of Light,
We are the holders of hope,
In the very heart of shadow
We are the lamps that guide the way.

Text_lang: <gasps quietly>
<exhales>

Text1_lang: It's a first step.
The rest is just time...
and trust.
<labored breathing>
Slender is the strand that guides your destiny...
So easily overlooked,
yet cutting deeper than the sharpest blade.
<labored breathing>
Shhhh.
It's almost over.
<labored breathing>
Your ambition was rare, you know.
Yet despite even betraying your own mother, here you are.
You - promised...
Nothing.
Yet, I gave you everything.
You were just...
not...enough.
Don't you...pity me..!
I don't.
You were a means to an end.
Your survival wasn't necessary.
I simply wish you had lasted a little longer.
<labored breathing>
And now you learn the true lesson of the Void...
Only the strongest survive.
<choking weakly>
<dying breath>

Text_lang: What--
What is happening?

Text1_lang: It's Beledar,
our star.
It shifts between the Light and...
this.
The dawntowers hold back the darkness with the Sacred Flame.
But the Light always returns.
The stars are devoured,
and they light a candle.
You know how this ends, Alleria.
Inevitably...
the Void consumes everything.
Show yourself monster!
You know where to find me...
...deeper in the darkness.
So much chaos and destruction...

Text_lang: We have to regroup.
Has anyone seen Khadgar?
No...

Text1_lang: We... will grieve him in time.
But Thrall is right.
Without reinforcements, we're at Xal'atath's mercy.
But no matter what she's planning,
we MUST stop her.

Text_lang: Jaina and I will rally the Alliance and the Horde,
but it will take some time for us to sail back here.
Right.
In the meantime, we'll stay here and keep the survivors safe.

Text1_lang: You will.
Not me.

Text_lang: Alleria, we need your--

Text1_lang: No. You don't.
I can't keep anyone safe.
But I can hunt down Xal'atath...
...and make her pay.

Text_lang: <grunt>
We heard ya!
We're here to help!
<painful groaning>
What's happening to them?
A skardyn transformation in progress!
Fascinating...
Stay back, lad!
<shocked gasp>
<unintelligible shouting>
Get away from him!
<angry yell>
<pained groan>
Gran'da!
That surge of energy--
the skardyn's reaction--
how did you do that?
I don't... know...
We'll figure it out later!
I can hear more coming...

Text1_lang: How... how could any Arathi be in league with such monsters?
The Sacred Flame is lost!
Fall back!
No!
We cannot keep retreating from the darkness!
Our fear has overshadowed our faith.
Beledar may have guided us, but it is not what will save us.
Stand with me against the shadow!
Show this Harbinger the true strength of the Arathi.
And if you fall against the darkness,
what will we do then?
It's what we always say, General,
the Light will return.
Even if someone else carries the torch.
We are the seekers of Light.
We are the holders of hope.
In the very heart of shadow...
Together, we guide the way.

Text_lang: Alleria...

Text1_lang: Khadgar?

Text_lang: This isn't... the real fight...

Text1_lang: <shocked gasp>
The Black Blood...
it's all around us.

Text_lang: <battle grunt>

Text1_lang: Turalyon. I...
I have to go.

Text_lang: What?
The battle is about to turn!

Text1_lang: We've played right into Xal'atath's hands.
But I know where she is.
And I'm going to stop her.

Text_lang: I'm coming with you!

Text1_lang: I know you would.
But your place is here.
I need you to trust me.

Text_lang: We'll be right with her.
Come back to me.

Text1_lang: I always do.

Text_lang: Pack it up, team! I know when we're beaten...

Text1_lang: Facility reactivated!

Text_lang: <grunt>
What are ye trying to tell us?
The great titan Khaz'goroth, who granted me the gift of the forge, has relayed information from the Pantheon about our purpose.
To create order from the chaos of the cosmos, the titans searched the Great Dark Beyond for the Prime Worldsoul.
This Worldsoul--the most powerful in existence--they would guide to become the greatest titan of all.
In time, they came to sense a mighty presence within the world called Azeroth.
The Pantheon made their way to the nascent Worldsoul, hoping that their search was at an end.

Text1_lang: Amazing... It's as though Keeper Archaedas was delivering the word of the great Khaz'goroth himself.
These logs must be the Architect's personal records of...everything. I wonder how many more we can recover.

Text_lang: I know of Archaedas from my studies in Khaz Modan... but this Worldsoul he speaks of... here on Azeroth...
Do you think that's what Gran'da Magni was hearing all those years when he was the Speaker?

Text1_lang: I am not sure what significance this might have for my people--or my purpose--but I have faith in the titans' plan for us.

Text_lang: On Azeroth, the Pantheon sensed a powerful source of corruption. To protect the Worldsoul, they sent us, the keepers, to lead the titanforged forces into battle.
In time, we rooted out and defeated the threat, imprisoning its last vestiges in the deep places of the world.
Then, led by Aman'Thul himself, the titans set toward studying the soul of Azeroth to determine whether it truly was the one they sought.
To aid the titans, we keepers were tasked with engineering the Manifold--a vast, world-spanning complex of machines, forges and installations.
Working in tandem, they would bring order to Azeroth, and create a means by which the Pantheon could examine the Worldsoul in depth.
That corruption the keeper's talking about... that's the Old Gods. That must be why they were here as well--for the power of the Worldsoul...
Though I've also read that while the titans defeated the Old Gods, they tore a wound in the world. Always thought that was just a metaphor.

Text1_lang: It seems clear now that Azeroth must be the Prime Worldsoul.
That would explain why the Void, the titans... the Legion... every cosmological force... have sought to control it--or destroy it--over the eons.

Text_lang: What do you suppose the titans needed to study about it?

Text1_lang: We cannot possibly understand the intricacies of the titans' reasons. But that complex Archaedas mentioned--I believe I know what that is about...

Text_lang: At the titans' command, we keepers began the Acclimation. Each installation, all linked to the Manifold, produced vast numbers of titanforged workers.
We fired the Great Forges, to fuel the Acclimation and empower the Manifold to heal the ravaged world.
Then began construction of the Coreway, a direct channel to the heart of Azeroth, that would allow the titans to study the Worldsoul without harming it.
However, as we delved deeper, we encountered certain obstacles--colossal crystals which we came to realize were calcified chunks of the Worldsoul's essence.
They are of great power, and I wonder how many yet remain undiscovered beneath the earth, all over the world.
By word of the great Khaz'goroth, the titans' research has revealed that Azeroth's Worldsoul is indeed the Prime. Our purpose may yet be fulfilled.
Enormous powerful chunks of Worldsoul essence... do you think Beledar, in Hallowfall, could be one of them?

Text1_lang: Potentially. But it was never within the scope of our Edicts to study the crystal.

Text_lang: He mentions the titanforged making the Coreway... did you know it was built to study the Worldsoul?

Text1_lang: We were created for the great purpose of serving the titans, and thus we built it. Its purpose was irrelevant to us.
We fulfilled our Edicts dependably, and we have strived to do so throughout the millennia, despite Khaz Algar facing many... setbacks.

Text_lang: Setbacks? What do you mean?

Text1_lang: Long ago, the continents of the world split apart, and the machinery that powered our facility was damaged--cut off from the Manifold.
We were unable to repair the connection. We operated on auxiliary power for a time... but eventually it ran out, and we fell into... disarray.

Text_lang: That must have been the Sundering... it's miraculous that any of this survived intact.
The great Khaz'goroth revealed to me that the corrupting influence of the imprisoned Old Gods was affecting the Worldsoul.
To protect it, we had the earthen construct the Worldcore--a vast chamber at the heart of the world. There, the Worldsoul will slumber, with only the titans to influence it.
I must note a disturbing development. As they worked to greater depths, some earthen began to behave erratically. This could not be countenanced.
Most units were repaired, and continued their work. But some began to physically change, and crystallize. They named themselves "thraegar."
These faulty units were so greatly affected that they rebelled against us, attacking and damaging the Worldcore.
In the course of studying them, it was determined that long exposure to the Worldsoul's energies led to the changes exhibited in their core directives.
If we cannot prevent this from happening, it will prove catastrophic to not only the Worldcore, but to the Manifold itself. Measures must be taken.

Text1_lang: I... do not recall this happening. That should not be. This "Worldcore" seems as if it was a monumental undertaking.
And the earthen malfunctioning? How would the Worldsoul's "energy" cause that? This is very confusing.

Text_lang: By the way, what does he mean by "repaired?"

Text1_lang: Unclear... But what he said about the thraegar rebelling is most disturbing.

Text_lang: The thraegar? That's what they called gran'da when he first got to Khaz Algar!

Text1_lang: We regard them as legendary champions, almost demigods... to learn that their directives were just... corrupted? That they were anomalies?
Was everything we believed mistaken... or even... a lie?

Text_lang: Wait--you don't suppose... if the earthen were affected by the Worldsoul's "radiation," the closer they got to it...
Could it be that it was actually trying to reach your people? Asking for help, like it did with my grand'da?
And undoing their directives... was it actually giving them free will?

Text1_lang: I... do not know.

Text_lang: With the danger posed by the rogue thraegar, the great Aman'Thul ordered the rebellion to be quelled and the thraegar hunted down until the threat was neutralized.
However, the issue of earthen malfunction under the influence of the Worldsoul's energies remained, and so a new solution was devised.
The earthen of Khaz Algar will relinquish their memories into an Archive to preserve recorded data, and purge the influence of the Worldsoul's energies.
By initiating this protocol on a regular cadence, we will ensure the thraegar malfunction does not take hold again.
To secure compliance, the titans have programmed Edicts into the operational earthen to regulate and enforce their discreet functions and efficiency.
Thus, the earthen will maintain the integrity of the Coreway and the machines of Khaz Algar. Should the Edicts be broken, more permanent failsafes have been set into place.
With these difficulties behind them, the titans have declared that the Worldsoul remains, dreaming, safely contained within the Worldcore, where no harm will come to it.
I do not know why I commit this information to the Archive--why I risk its discovery in the future. Perhaps the Worldsoul's influence does not extend solely to the earthen.
What we've learned here... It calls the entire history of Azeroth into question. What if... what if our history isn't what they said it was?

Text1_lang: So the keepers stole our memories, and let us believe that it was for our own good? That it was so we could continue to fulfill our purpose--no, not even our purpose!
We built the greatest structures the world has ever seen, and they set us to become... maintenance drones, just... cogs in a machine.

Text_lang: And it does seem that they did it to keep you complacent... obedient. Following their Edicts--and eliminating those of you they couldn't control.

Text1_lang: Those Edicts... they were bonds of servitude. And we never even knew.
And then when the Sundering happened, we were cut off from all of it--and Archaedas never returned to help us. Why didn't he return?
Our entire history--our culture--held in that Archive... I want my memories back. I want ALL our memories back. Damn the titans.

Text_lang: I'm starting to think there's more to the Worldsoul than the titans wanted us to know. That they had other plans for it-- and Azeroth--than we were led to believe.
What if all of us--even Archaedas himself--have been deceived?
And so the battle is won. $n, all of Khaz Algar owes you a tremendous debt.
When you first arrived on our shores, we were fractured and divided. But you showed us the path to becoming whole again.

Text1_lang: You reignited our drive for purpose, and to define the parameters of our own existence.
We see now that traditions can change and evolve... and even be broken, if necessary.
The Arathi no longer cower in darkness. We bring the Light in our hearts wherever we go.

Text_lang: This Council stands stronger than ever before, with new friends and allies by our side. And we have you to thank for it.
Alleria. When I heard about Dalaran, I...
I would have come sooner. I wanted to. But the state of the world right now... the Radiant Song...

Text1_lang: It's alright, Turalyon. You don't... We each have our responsibilities to bear.
Truth be told, if you had seen me as I was... what I had started to become...

Text_lang: I should have been there for you.

Text1_lang: You were. More than you could ever know.

Text_lang: We stood together for a thousand years. I'll stand by you for a thousand more.

Text1_lang: And the next time I push you away?

Text_lang: I wait until you ask me to come back.

Text1_lang: Then it's a good thing I always do.

Text_lang: I've missed you, Alleria. And I'm not going anywhere.

Text1_lang: I know. We stand together, Turalyon. Here and now.

Text_lang: I feel the earthen have come a long way since last we were here in the Archive.

Text1_lang: A factual statement. When I first answered your queries, the Archive was lost to us. As were the Stonevault and Awakening Machine.
But now we have a future. And slowly we will also have our past. Largely we have you and your "clan" to thank for it.

Text_lang: Ye needn't mention it, High Speaker. I'm just glad ye'll be around for... as long as ye were meant to be.

Text1_lang: Thank you. I will admit that I approach that prospect with some trepidation.
The earthen that are emerging from the Stonevault will take our culture to the ends of Azeroth, but...
Who knows what lurks here in our past? What will we uncover about our purpose and the titans?

Text_lang: I hadna thought o' that. Well, come what may, I'll be here to help ye.

Text1_lang: Your continued assistance is appreciated. I feel... you have made me feel as though I am part of your "clan."

Text_lang: To properly be part o' my clan ye'd have to marry my Gran'da or the like. But that would nae work for many reasons.

Text1_lang: Brinthe looks puzzled.

Text_lang: That was a joke, Brinthe. Ye'll always be part o' my clan--blood, water, or stone.
It occurs to me that I never got the chance to properly thank you, $p.
Were it not for your efforts, Dalaran could have proven to be an even greater tragedy than it was.

Text1_lang: We thought we had lost you, Khadgar. How did you survive?

Text_lang: The Dark Heart was created not to destroy, but to capture and harness all manner of power.
When I felt what it was doing to me, I transmuted myself into pure arcane energy...

Text1_lang: ...and allowed yourself to be trapped within the Dark Heart.

Text_lang: Yes. Until you freed me.

Text1_lang: That was a risky move. Trusting me to finish the fight against Xal'atath.

Text_lang: I knew you would do whatever it took to defeat her. Just like all those years ago...
...when we charged through the Dark Portal and closed it behind us to save our world.
Both then and now, placing my faith in you was never any risk at all.
That transmutation spell, however... that was not without consequences.
You know, Kurdran keeps saying I should just ride a gryphon around.
That seems terribly inconvenient, if you ask me. I much prefer this chair.

Text1_lang: Could that be because Archmage Modera designed it for you herself?

Text_lang: Why Alleria, whatever are you implying?

Text1_lang: Only that you and Turalyon are so very alike: bold in battle, shy in matters of the heart.

Text_lang: Hah! And you are still the same old Alleria, I see.

Text1_lang: That I am, Khadgar. Void, or no Void.

Text_lang: <enraged hiss>

Text1_lang: Our group was attacked within a delve by a monster named Zekvir.
He is the Hand of the Harbinger... Xal'atath.
There's something within the delves that she doesn't want people to find.

Text_lang: You are not alone, friends.
This is the realm of the Machine!
And I... am the High... Speaker!
I almost forgot I sent you away...
the Awakening Machine!
Outlanders, you may wander where you will,
but when you are done, return from whence you came.
Ha! I have you cornered now, you pilfering little weave-trash!

Text1_lang: Gracious. The little fly thinks he's a proper spider, but he cannot even tell when he's caught in a web.

Text_lang: By the-- who do you think you are? I'll have you know I am one of Ansurek's most prized--

Text1_lang: You seem to be laboring under the assumption that I care a wit for who you claim to be. I do not. But I WILL tell you who I am. And I will tell you what you are.
I am the Widow Arak'nai, the stewardess of Queen Neferess' legacy and the one who weaves the threads of a free Azj-Kahet. And you, Meesk, are nothing more than a trifling supper.
Come now, my little ones. It is dinner time.

Text_lang: No... Stay back...! AHHHH!

Text1_lang: How pitiful. Come, my little morsel. Let us return to more pleasant webs. You've done well.

Text_lang: <Angry hissing>
Take a step back. This here is a trap.
Brann Bronzebeard and the Explorers' League! Cease your explorations.
Otherwise you shall face Zekvir, Hand of the Harbinger. We are watching. We are waiting.
Ye better believe we won't be stopping! I'll continue exploring tae see if I can find out who exactly this "Zekvir" is.

Text1_lang: War Golems are active and back in production.
<amused chuckle>

Text_lang: <Laborious battle cries.>
So... what now?
We rebuild. But not just brick and mortar. We need changes to our foundation--to us.

Text1_lang: Agreed. We must move forward with intention. And learn from the mistakes we were too prideful to before.

Text_lang: I admit I was blinded by the ivory towers of Dalaran... I believed the Kirin Tor's wisdom was nigh infallible.
Let us pledge then that the new Kirin Tor will be different. No more councils, no more floating cities, and no more meddling in world affairs.

Text1_lang: Then we are all in agreement. We will start anew. For the Kirin Tor. For all of us.

Text_lang: Good. Because this old man is tired. I will go to Dornogal to rest. And then start rebuilding the connections we have lost.
I look forward to our future as the Kirin Tor... and friends.

Text1_lang: Are you going to stay, Kalecgos?

Text_lang: The Dragon Isles can endure a little longer without me. We have much work to do.
More mages are arriving to lend their strength. We need to start planning how we want to spend our resources.
Dalaran's destruction almost destroyed me. But it is not an end, it is an opportunity--to do things right this time.
We shall build our strength not from dominion or deceit, but from dedication to learning and magic.
Thrall nods to Lufsela with respect.
Well, best be setting sail to Ironforge. No sense in dawdling.

Text1_lang: Are you sure about staying, Dagran? You could return home with us and study there...

Text_lang: I'm sure, ma. There's still so much knowledge here yet to be discovered!

Text1_lang: And knowing you, you'll find it all. Keep out of trouble, and make sure Brinthe always knows where ye are.

Text_lang: Yes, mum.
Ach, and who's this?

Text1_lang: I am called Orweyna. I've been told you too have heard the voice of the goddess.

Text_lang: Goddess? You mean Azeroth? Aye- I was her speaker for many years, but she's let me go from that service.

Text1_lang: Her voice has led me far from my home, seeking a truth I know she wishes to reveal, but my kin, they... do not understand.

Text_lang: Aye. It can be lonely, followin' a path that others can't see. But don't make the same mistake I did, puttin' it all on yourself.
Look for those who will walk the path with you. If I've learned anythin', it's that we'll always need each other to not lose ourselves on the journey.

Text1_lang: You are kind, Magni. I will consider your words carefully.

Text_lang: Best of luck to you, Orweyna. One day when you've found what you're looking for, I hope you too find your way home.

Text1_lang: Are you sure about staying, Dagran? You could return home with us and study there...
<laughs> And knowing you, you'll find it all.
Keep out of trouble, and make sure Brinthe always knows where ye are.
What are you making? You seem... inspired.

Text_lang: This morning, the Siren Crystal sang a reverent hymn to me... a restorative anthem from a bygone age.

Text1_lang: That sounds like the kind of inspiration we'd receive from Beledar.

Text_lang: Yes! Its music soothed me. Now I'm crafting more healing crystals. They'll bring solace to our Empire.
Hey, what's the good news?

Text1_lang: The Siren Crystal... it was making a racket this morning! Like a pot banging in my head! Still, it gave me some ideas...

Text_lang: Yeah yeah yeah, you've got a headache. But, ah, whatcha makin'? We found you a whole kit and kaboodle of crystals!

Text1_lang: I'm boostin' their energy! You could make some powerful artifacts with these babies!
You seem fascinated with those crystals. I was watching your process earlier. What is it about them that inspires you?
This morning, I heard the Siren Crystal sing to me, ringing with an intricate melody.
Perhaps it was calling to the spark of the Worldsoul within you. We've been searching the island to learn more.
Your thoughts align with mine. If we found more of the smaller crystals, I could make enduring wonderworks.

Text_lang: Look, pal! The only opportunity here is the one I gave you.
Big things are coming, and if you want to be part of it, you better fall in line.
Jastor Gallywix is back in business!
What you have told me makes me afraid for you, Aethas.
Fear isn't part of it. Or... not fear of nerubians or... or even Xal'atath.
Then of what?
Of letting everyone we have lost down again. If I slip. If... if I sleep. What then?
What horror comes here and takes more of us away?
I know very little about what has transpired here. But...
Aethas, none of it was your fault.
You're a survivor--a victim of this tragedy.
To continue to fight and then rebuild... that's more than anyone would ask of you.
And yet, here I am. Still alone. The Kirin Tor...
They will come.
For now, you need rest. Let me put the burden on my wings for awhile.
Kalecgos, I... thank you.
Jaina, I thought you were staying to help in the Tranquil Strand.

Text1_lang: I was. But we should speak about the future of the Kirin Tor sooner rather than later.

Text_lang: I'm afraid the news from outside is bleak. We lost all but a few after amassing at Dalaran.

Text1_lang: Then... our new Kirin Tor is over before it began.

Text_lang: No, the mages who have answered the call... We have an opportunity. No council. No rank.

Text1_lang: Like starting over? Returning to study and research?
But we have a duty to protect the Alliance--and Azeroth.

Text_lang: We can still fulfill that mission by investigating. Training. Advising.

Text1_lang: It would keep us mobile and decentralized. A tragedy like Dalaran would not happen again.

Text_lang: Safety is a benefit, yes.

Text1_lang: Study and passing on my knowledge appeals to me. But I have to think about the ramifications of such a drastic change.

Text_lang: And that is why it should be you who starts putting the pieces back together.

Text1_lang: Khadgar...

Text_lang: I need rest, Jaina. But... I promise I won't stay away for long.

Text1_lang: Meryl can assist me. Aethas should have a key role as well. I will go back and speak to them.

Text_lang: Thank you, Jaina. And good luck.

Text1_lang: Excellent. That's the kind of support we'll need to bolster our troops. We could strengthen our defenses.

Text_lang: I didn't hear a call to battle. I heard a hymn of healing.
I don't want to go to war again. I want to go home. We're closer to our homelands than ever before.

Text1_lang: We're not going to war. It's coming to us. When the others seize that Crystal, we'll need more guards.

Text_lang: You need to trust the earthen and the goblins. They're not our enemies. We need to work together.

Text1_lang: That's the difference between you and me. You build. I protect. And mark my words: we will need that protection.
It's a shame the Kul Tirans didn't hear the same song. We found the remains of their mining camp. Their culture didn't endure here.
Really? I haven't left the workshop. What have you found? Journals? Letters? Schematics?
More mysteries. Their culture practically vanished overnight. It's one of the Crystal's biggest enigmas.
I heard they were mining Azerite. I'm glad we have more reasonable designs.
Now I have the inspiration for more intricate creations: lattices, orreries, matrices...
Spoken like a true earthen. A creator should follow her heart. We'll find more of those smaller crystals for you.

Text_lang: You know what you should do? Make some explosives! Big bada booms!
Didya know what was here before us, Didi? An Azerite mine! Some Kul Tiran outfit...

Text1_lang: Hey, I ain't lookin' to blow stuff up. I want a power source... a bunch of batteries!

Text_lang: Okay, okay, I get ya. After all, whatcha got cookin' could be really valuable.

Text1_lang: I ain't in it for the money. I'm in it for the power.

Text_lang: Soon, you'll have more power than you know what to do with.

Text1_lang: Oh, believe you me, I know what to do with it. Heh heh heh heh.

Text_lang: That's our Didi! No off position on the genius switch!

Text1_lang: Hannan?

Text_lang: This was a mistake, Orweyna.
You've put us all in grave peril.

Text1_lang: Our goddess is crying out for aid,

Text_lang: We followed you and your visions this far,

Text1_lang: It is those very traditions that have put our home at risk!
You've seen the growing threats here, Hannan.
We cannot give up now.

Text_lang: The others and I are returning to the cradle to seek forgiveness.

Text1_lang: <Takes a deep breath.>
Tell the elders that the fault is mine, and mine alone. I will face them in time...but for now,

Text_lang: Then you will walk it alone.
I do not understand your conviction, Orweyna.
May the ancient roots of our people ever thrive beneath your steps.

Text1_lang: Goodbye, Hannan.

Text_lang: He's broken audio playback, but just temporarily

Text1_lang: Where are the others?

Text_lang: Coming here, revealing ourselves to the mortals, getting caught in their affairs.

Text1_lang: how can we not answer?

Text_lang: but we cannot break the haranir's traditions any longer.

Text1_lang: <sighs quietly>

Text_lang: You owe it to them to face the elders by their side.

Text1_lang: my path is here.

Text_lang: But...I do admire it.

Text1_lang: While Bargus repairs the outer chassis, let us take a closer look at the destabilized matrices in this fractured crystal, shall we?
Stabilization complete. The crystals inner matrices begin humming with power!
Your conduct is unacceptable.

Text_lang: My... ascension...
Text1_lang: My... ascension...

Text_lang: Your ascent ends here!
Text1_lang: Your ascent ends here!

Text_lang: Witness the fury of Maldraxxus!
Text1_lang: Witness the fury of Maldraxxus!

Text_lang: Was just... getting... started...
Text1_lang: Was just... getting... started...
You shall go no further.

Text_lang: Useless... bones...
Text1_lang: Useless... bones...

Text_lang: Fight!
Text1_lang: Fight!

Text_lang: You will be forgotten!
Text1_lang: You will be forgotten!

Text_lang: Meet your demise!
Text1_lang: Meet your demise!

Text_lang: Don't... chop me... up...
Text1_lang: Don't... chop me... up...

Text_lang: Face me!
Text1_lang: Face me!

Text_lang: You are in over your head!
Text1_lang: You are in over your head!

Text_lang: I will enjoy destroying you.
Text1_lang: I will enjoy destroying you.
Resistance is ill-advised.

Text_lang: My legend begins!
Text1_lang: My legend begins!
Prepare for combat.
This will end quickly.

Text_lang: So this... is defeat...
Text1_lang: So this... is defeat...

Text_lang: Time to earn my glory!
Text1_lang: Time to earn my glory!

Text_lang: Still... more... to learn...
Text1_lang: Still... more... to learn...

Text_lang: Intruders? Find them!
You'll fall to my swarm!
Gather my prey to me!
My swarm hungers!
My watch... ends...

Text1_lang: Once, my people thrived under the guidance of the Black Empire.
Queen Neferess refused to reclaim that glory. But no more.
Ansurek and the Black Blood will usher in a new age for Azj-Kahet!
The harvest will prevail!
Void take you all!
What weak blood.
Harvested.
My blood... weeps...
I told you that you were destined for great things. Rejoice, for you have aided the end of all things.
Ah, you've arrived. Our "friend" awaits you in the High Hollows.

Text_lang: Our queen offers a most wondrous gift. We will become greater than we are.
Invaders! Fear not, citizens. We will show them Ansurek's wrath.
Do you not know who I am? Whose voice you challenge?
Come! Let us speak.
Bow before me!
We revel in your fear!
Azj-Kahet will thrive!
Your terror is our victory!
Blessed silence.
Bend the knee!
We rise through conquest!
Should have listened.
My... beautiful... voice...

Text1_lang: Buffoon. Not even worthy of the fifth strand.
Ansurek has eyes everywhere. You'll need to blind them to meet the Vizier.

Text_lang: Enough!
You primitives have a funny scent but you sure can fight!
Look, maybe we can make a deal, huh? I'll pass you these perfumes I can't sell and I get to keep my head.
By the weave! One of Ansurek's spies has fallen.
I know. Poor thing. Those rags must have been spun with last season's web.
Text1_lang: I know. Poor thing. Those rags must have been spun with last season's web.

Text_lang: Another spy has fallen? This cannot be!
That poor Ulthik brood. None of their hatchlings were chosen for Ascension.
Text1_lang: That poor Ulthik brood. None of their hatchlings were chosen for Ascension.

Text_lang: If this distressing trend continues, we will run out of spies!
Your target is the Grand Splicer, Izo. Her drive for innovation meshed well with Ansurek's thirst for Ascension.
Stay close and be quiet.
The Transformatory was once the home of our sacred evolution.
Izo has made a mockery of our traditions, at the queen's comm--
Tsk tsk tsk. Dear Nizrek, a traitor? Our queen will be so disappointed.

Text1_lang: First, your little pets will die. Then we'll make you speak.

Text_lang: I'll take it from here.
Twilight approaches...

Text1_lang: ...and the frost bites!
Seems it's my turn.
Glacial annihilation.
The blizzard surges...

Text_lang: ...and darkness consumes!
My turn.

Text1_lang: Must I do everything?
Your blood will freeze!

Text_lang: Lost in the dark.
You won't be missed.
Are you finished?
Shadows... take... me...

Text1_lang: So... cold...

Text_lang: Thank you. Would that I could do more to repay you, but this is as far as I go.
Our strands are strong! None will pass!

Text1_lang: Overcrawlers? I've enough of you in my collection. Begone.
Hm. You're... interesting.
All failure breeds success eventually... wouldn't you agree?
Let's see which of the two you are.
The pursuit of perfection can be... messy. But worthwhile in the end.
So persistent. For you, a reward--witness the unparalleled wonder of transformation.
Enough! You've earned a place in my collection. Let me usher you in.
Witness the glory of our Ascension!
The possibilities are endless!
How will you adapt?
Grant me the strength of a lord!
One with the weave!
Survival of the fittest!
What can I make of you?
A sage's wisdom is required!
Consider the variables.
Too late!
I'll break you beneath me!
How primitive.
A fresh specimen.
The strongest survive!
This is... inconceivable...

Text_lang: Ansurek will be absolutely furious when she learns of Izo's demise. I cannot wait to witness it.

Text1_lang: I have maps of Azeroth, but you probably don't wa--
You have maps of big world? I want maps of big world!
Okay then. Rope, hooks, maps. Anything else?
You have candle?
Sure, I can throw in a candle for free for you.
You give candle? I... take candle?
Sure.
This best day ever.

Text_lang: See? We're late to the party. Meet me below. And watch your step! Heh heh heh.
Hey, welcome aboard! The earthen and the Arathi are on the island already. We gotta catch up!

Wouldn't you and half of Khaz Algar want to know! 

First the Arathi and earthen are all askin' about it, then next thing you know, they're heading off in their airships and mole machines! 

Oh, if I still had my rocket drill contacts, I betcha I coulda gotten us there faster!

But fine, ya wanna know? 

We're headin' to the Siren Isle. Ever heard of it?

Almost nothin', unfortunately. I put my best guys on it to see what they could dig up.

They didn't find much; just a few tales from Boralus. The oldest record we could find was some Kul Tiran fable or somethin' warning us of the dangers of 'The Call', whatever that means. 

Couldn't find any charts or nothin'. Seems like a place most have steered clear from, but it sounds like an opportunity if ya ask me!

Thankfully Ricket and my ground crew gave us enough data to work with so we could find our way back.

Text1_lang:
You headin' to the Siren Isle?

<Du'una grimaces around her tusks and spits.>

I told Cableclamp dis is a bad omen. I've heard stories about de sirens. In zandali, we call dem "bwon'tulak." Death Singers. Terrible creatures.

I am blessed. I never encountered dem before in all my time flyin' over de seas. But now we're headin' for a place named after dem?

<Du'una bows and shakes her head.>

May Shango guide de winds.

Text_lang:
Feels good to be back on de open air!

Never felt right after we all went on strike with Cableclamp. Her contractors weren't payin' any of us--her included! So she brought the Princess down. Eventually we went our own separate ways for a while.

But we be back and ready to fly! Ha ha!

Except Du'una. She's afraid of de bwon'tulak, which I don't blame her. 

We're sailin' right into stormy weathers, but Shango always watchin' over us in de storms!

Text1_lang: The stars of this time are bent on new paths, beacons of hope and strength for the coming ages.

Text_lang: <Marmaduke looks at you expectantly.>
<Marmaduke looks at you longingly.>

Text1_lang: I do not understand what you want me to see.
